{"commentv2": 1, "number": 0, "id": 399532, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "Icecoldcoke", "body": "I guess I'll be the first to point out the obvious.\r\n\r\nMalygos is the only boss and only hostile creature in the Eye of Eternity 10 and 25man raid in Wrath of the Lich King.\r\n\r\nThis raid is for level 80 players in almost to full naxxramas gear. \r\n\r\nIt's the third raid instance (gear wise / difficulty) that players will visit with the first two being Naxxramas and Obsidian Sanctum.\r\n\r\nThe encounter requires one member of your raid to have completed the quest from http://wotlk.wowhead.com/?item=44569 for the 10man version of the encounter, or http://wotlk.wowhead.com/?item=44577 for the 25man version of the encounter. They are both drops from Sapphiron, with the heroic key being from 25man Naxx, and the non-heroic key being from 10man Naxx.\r\n\r\nThe enouncter has three phases which present interesting challenges for the raid. \r\n\r\nBeing the first raid on your server to kill Malygos in the heroic(25man) version of the raid will be rewarded with the achievement http://wotlk.wowhead.com/?achievement=1400, getting a unique title that only your raid will have, and the server gets broadcasted letting everyone know of your achievement!", "date": "2008-10-07T18:36:12-05:00", "rating": 139, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "[quote=\"Bent\"]You don't need to have completed the quest started from http://wotlk.wowhead.com/?item=44569 you'll just need someone with the key. The item that is required to complete det quest actually drops from Malygos, so that would be like Maiden dropped Karazhan key.[/quote]  Actually you do need to complete that quest to receive [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=44582]Key to the Focusing Iris[/url] which summons Malygos.  The item you quoted drops from Sapphiron, not Malygos.  The quest you then have on follow up is [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=13384]Judgment at the Eye of Eternit", "creationdate": "2008-10-07T18:36:13-05:00", "id": 389669, "rating": 2, "commentid": 399532, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "DSXC", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "A phase 3 rotation that I would highly recommend that has worked well for me and my guild:  3, 1, 1, wait for 90+ energy and then choose your finisher based on situation. - Not in danger: 2 - Big nasty nuke being cast on you: 1, wait for the moment the cast in finished, then 5*. Not before and preferably not too late.  * DO NOT \"SPAM CLICK\" THE FLAME SHIELD KEY. * I tested and confirmed that if you spam, it's duration will be cut extremely short. To be safe, do not use any skills right before needing to use this ability.  Repeat above unless low on life. If low on life: - Target self, 3 then 4", "creationdate": "2008-10-07T18:36:13-05:00", "id": 370221, "rating": 0, "commentid": 399532, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "94427", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "You don't need to have completed the quest started from  http://wotlk.wowhead.com/?item=44569 you'll just need someone with the key. The item that is required to complete det quest actually drops from Malygos, so that would be like Maiden dropped Karazhan key.", "creationdate": "2009-02-10T10:33:43-06:00", "id": 387362, "rating": 2, "commentid": 399532, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Bent", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-10-07T18:38:45-05:00", 1, "Icecoldcoke"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 1, "id": 407089, "nreplies": 10, "sticky": 0, "user": "shadowspa", "body": "Strategies\r\nPhase One\r\n\r\nDuring Phase One, Malygos is tanked in the center of the room by one tank.\r\n\r\nHis attacks hit hard, but the attack speed is slow. He does arcane breaths for X damage.\r\n\r\nThroughout the fight, power sparks come out of portals outside of the platform, they slowly move to Malygos, and if they hit him his next arcane breath does a VERY HIGH amount of damage, most likely one-shotting your tank. It's important that they are killed before they hit him. When the power sparks are killed, they drop a small aura on the ground that increases your damage done. The aura stacks, so if they all die in that same location, you can get very high hits off.\r\n\r\nTrick: The sparks can be \"pulled\" to your DPS with Death Grip, so it advisable to have a pre-assigned stack location for your raid, and have a Death Knight pull the sparks to that spot. Once pulled they are rootable to keep them in place while you kill them.\r\n\r\nMalygos also uses a cyclone ability that will pull the entire raid into the air and spin them around. He will not attack your tank during this ability, however power sparks will continue to move toward him, make sure you kill them if they are going to get too close to him. Once this ability ends, Malygos will be facing in a random direction and your tank will also be in a random location, so it is vital to move intelligently at this point before he is once again facing your tank, as his breath will one-shot any dps or healers unlucky enough to be in the wrong place.\r\n\r\nNote: Once Malygos reaches 50%, he will slowly take off, however he remains targetable until he reaches his max height, so burn him as best you can while he is taking off.\r\nPhase Two\r\n\r\nPhase Two begins at 50%.\r\n\r\nMalygos himself is not targetable during this phase, it will end when the adds he spawns are all killed. However, he does continue to play a part in the encounter.\r\n\r\nDuring this phase he drops anti-magic zones onto the ground the raid MUST stand inside of, it reduces magical damage taken by 50%. They shrink over time, so it's important that your raid moves to each new one he drops.\r\n\r\nThroughout the phase, he will deep breath doing ~4k damage per second, unless you are standing inside of the anti-magic zone.\r\n\r\nThe way the fight works during this phase is there are NPCs riding around on disks in the room. There are two types of mobs, Lords and Scions. The Lords will move down onto the group, and need to be tanked (They will one-shot a non-tank). After they die, they drop a disk that a raid member can mount onto, which allows them to fly, to attack the Scions that do not come down to the ground. It is recommended to let melee take the first disks, then ranged. As those mobs die, they also drop disks, which allows the rest of your dps to get onto them. The Scions will continually cast Arcane Blast on random targets on the floor, which is mitigated by the anti-magic zones. While mounted on a disk, you will not take damage.\r\n\r\nAfter all of the NPCs riding on the disks die, the players on the disks need to dismount as Phase 3 is about to begin.\r\n\r\nNote: After all the Scions are dead, you will get a short burn period on Malygos before he breaks the floor. Use any DPS increase cooldowns that are available at this time, as you will not be able to use them once you mount your dragon. If executed well you can take an extra 5%-10% off his HP before you enter phase 3.\r\nPhase Three\r\n\r\nPhase Three begins when all of the Scions die (the Lords should be killed first, so they must be killed as well). Malygos destroys the floor of the room, and the raid falls onto dragons.\r\n\r\nThe dragons use combo points and energy sort of like a rogue. The combo points are used for special finishing moves.\r\n\r\nWarning : You are now entering an unclear phase's description, where things may be wrong, and not the correct strategy.\r\n\r\nDuring this phase Malygos does - In Melee Range... Heavy Melee Attacks and Cleaves RangedA high damage ranged ability (The focusing mentioned below)\r\n\r\nThe dragons have 6 abilities:\r\n\r\nFlame Spike\r\n    Damaging fire attack causing 943-1057 fire damage and awarding 1 combo point at the cost of 10 energy. \r\n\r\nEngulf in Flames\r\n    Finishing move which launches a blast of flame igniting target for 1500 fire damage every 3 seconds. The effect can stack and will last longer per combo point up to 22 seconds. Costs 50 energy. \r\n\r\nRevivify\r\n    A HoT that lasts for 10 seconds healing 500 per second and awarding 1 combo point at the cost of 10 energy. \r\n\r\nLife Burst\r\n    Huge healing finishing move which increases the casters healing done by 50% and lasts longer per combo point. Max combo points award a 15k heal over 25 seconds. Costs 50 energy. \r\n\r\nName N/A\r\n    Increases your drake's flight speed by 500%. \r\n\r\nFlame Shield\r\n    Finishing move to protect your drake. Shield surrounds you reducing all damage taken by 80% and lasting up to 6 seconds for max combo points. Costs 25 energy with a 30 second cooldown. \r\n\r\nThough the strategy for this phase is still unclear, it is believed that each player should target themselves and stack up 5 revivifys granting 5 total combo points on themselves, and then they should use Life Burst. eEfore Revivify fades, the player should recast it on themselves, same deal with life burst, but switching targets clears the combo points, so you will need to cast 5 more heals on yourself then life burst before it fades.\r\n\r\nIn between keeping your Hots up you should be Flame Spike spamming malygos, after 5 combo points apply Engulf in Flames, then spam it more times.\r\n\r\nWhenever he sets his \"focus\" to you, it's important that you have 5 combo points on him, and use your shield (hotkey 6). It is believed you can also use the sprint (hotkey 5) and outrange him before he begins channeling.\r\n\r\nNote: Remember to save 25 energy at all times to use your shield. If you are at 0 energy and targeted, you may be killed before you regen enough to use your shield. This is important as threat seems strange for this portion of the encounter and you may be targeted at any time.\r\nThe End\r\n\r\nThen you just burn him until the end of the fight, where Alexstrasza enters and finishes the battle. The loot for the fight comes from Alexstrasza's Gift, the fight rewards two badges.\r\n\r\nThe exit portal respawns, and you can fly over to it. But the floor of the instance does not respawn.\r\n\r\nQuotes\r\n\r\nPre-Fight:\r\n\r\n    * Lesser beings, intruding here! A shame that your excess courage does not compensate for your stupidity!\r\n    * None but the blue dragonflight are welcome here! Perhaps this is the work of Alexstrasza? Well then, she has sent you to your deaths.\r\n    * What could you hope to accomplish, to storm brassily into my domain? To employ MAGIC? Against ME? *Laughs*\r\n    * I am without limits here...the rules of your cherished reality do not apply...In this realm, I am in control...\r\n    * I give you one chance. Pledge loyalty to me, and perhaps I won't slaughter you for your insolence! \r\n\r\nAggro Phase 1:\r\n\r\n    * My patience has reached its limit, I WILL BE RID OF YOU! \r\n\r\nAggro Phase 2:\r\n\r\n    * Few have experienced the pain I will now inflict on you! \r\n\r\nAggro Phase 3:\r\n\r\n    * SUBMIT! \r\n\r\nEnd Phase 1:\r\n\r\n    * I had hoped to end your lives quickly, but you have proven more...resilient then I had anticipated. None the less, your efforts are in vain, it is you reckless, careless mortals who are to blame for this war! I do what I must...And if it means your...extinction...THEN SO", "date": "2008-10-15T16:28:53-05:00", "rating": 226, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Phase 1 arcane breath hits for around 20k in 10man ([url=http://wotlk.wowhead.com/?spell=56272]Arcane Breath[/url], I think).  25man ability is probably [url=http://wotlk.wowhead.com/?spell=60072]this one[/url].  The sparks appear to give a 50% damage increase to the boss.  Also note that arcane breath appears to be currently coded as [b]frost[/b] damage.  Great strat for dealing with sparks here!  To add, sparks seem to be susceptible to all stuns in the 10man variant.  Phase 2 deep breath does 5000 arcane-type damage every second, before mitigation from the anti-magic zone (10man).  Malygos ", "creationdate": "2008-10-15T16:28:54-05:00", "id": 355678, "rating": 30, "commentid": 407089, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "xander", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Though I haven't done the Malygos encounter itself, the phase 3 dragon abilities appear identical to those of Corastrasza's drakes in the quest Aces High! [url=http://wotlk.wowhead.com/?quest=13413][/url]", "creationdate": "2008-11-07T12:28:51-06:00", "id": 54869, "rating": 42, "commentid": 407089, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "241439", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "The unkown Drake ability is probably this one, Blazing Speed:  http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=57092", "creationdate": "2008-11-12T10:49:23-06:00", "id": 55654, "rating": 27, "commentid": 407089, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "max000000", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "That's not really relevant, but I cannot leave one of the coolest characters ever created by Blizz be treated like that! [quote]When dps died, [b]she[/b] berzerked for my group when we were almost done killing the adds.[/quote] It's a HE!", "creationdate": "2009-02-18T13:33:14-06:00", "id": 80920, "rating": 40, "commentid": 407089, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "64407", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Actually Dragon in Spanish (Drag\u00f3n) is male. So is in French.", "creationdate": "2009-08-27T17:12:25-05:00", "id": 118733, "rating": 13, "commentid": 407089, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "430025", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 2, "id": 407090, "nreplies": 5, "sticky": 0, "user": "shadowspa", "body": "End Phase 2:\r\n\r\n    * ENOUGH! If you intend to reclaim Azeroth's magic, then you shall have it... \r\n\r\nIntro Phase 3:\r\n\r\n    * Now your benefactors make their appearance...But they are too late. The powers contained here are powerful enough to destroy the world ten times over! What do you think they will do to you? \r\n\r\nHigh Damage Mode:\r\n\r\n    * I AM UNSTOPPABLE! \r\n\r\nBreath Attack:\r\n\r\n    * YOU WILL NOT SUCCEED WHILE I DRAW BREATH! \r\n\r\nSpell Cast:\r\n\r\n    * Still standing? Not for long...\r\n    * Your cause is lost!\r\n    * Your fragile mind will be shattered! \r\n\r\nLarge Attack in Phase 3:\r\n\r\n    * The powers at work here exceed anything you could possibly imagine! \r\n\r\nAnti-Magic Shell:\r\n\r\n    * I will teach you IGNORANT children just how little you know of magic... \r\n\r\nMagic Blast:\r\n\r\n    * Watch helplessly as your hopes are swept away... \r\n\r\nSlay Phase 1:\r\n\r\n    * Your stupidity has finally caught up to you!\r\n    * More artifacts to confiscate...\r\n    * *Laughs* How very...naive.. \r\n\r\nSlay Phase 2:\r\n\r\n    * Your energy will be put to good use!\r\n    * I AM THE SPELL WEAVER! My power is INFINITE!\r\n    * Your spirit will linger here forever! \r\n\r\nSlay Phase 3:\r\n\r\n    * Alexstrasza! Another of your brood falls!\r\n    * Little more then gnats!\r\n    * Your red allies will share your fate... \r\n\r\nDeath:\r\n\r\n    * UNTHINKABLE! The mortals will destroy...e-everything...my sister...what have you-", "date": "2008-10-15T16:29:27-05:00", "rating": 52, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "no - they aren't CREATED by Titans...they come from one kind... from one type of Ancestors...divided by time to different \"races\" like - all dog races came from wolfs origins  Titans only infused dragons with spark of their own power, because dragons was mightest and wisest from all creatures in that time  sister or brother is more that what it means this word is used by Dragons as Tittle (it means...YOU are EQUAL to me) you are more than one of my kind - we have the same purpose   they will call brother or sister even someone who will be ten genereations younger...if he will be on the same ra", "creationdate": "2008-10-15T16:29:28-05:00", "id": 438529, "rating": 10, "commentid": 407090, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Daralyn", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Yes....... but these is not all of his history. After adventure in book day of dragon he and all others aspects are fully strong , as they before of deathwing betrayal... and all goes their ways......and Malygos goes to the Coldarra .. But Tyrygosa see how bad Malygos feel, so she try to go to the outland to find nether dragons , cuz she think they help him with his madness... and she bring these nether dragons to him and they heal him or something do with him.....and after that he feel so much better .         But Malygos , now fully healthy he has shocked what other races doing with magic ,.", "creationdate": "2008-10-15T16:29:28-05:00", "id": 455791, "rating": 4, "commentid": 407090, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Zultian", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "meaning Alexstrasza is Malygos' sister?", "creationdate": "2009-10-28T19:58:50-05:00", "id": 129633, "rating": 14, "commentid": 407090, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "436033", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Alexstrasza is the mother of life, or  rather the guardian of life and therefore all living things in azeroth is seen by he as her brood. but you could say malygos is Alexstraszas brother, they are both made by the titans Alexstrasza was made by Eonar and malygos by Norgannon", "creationdate": "2009-12-29T16:05:41-06:00", "id": 140070, "rating": 10, "commentid": 407090, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "atrixia", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "True Malygos went insane because he was the last of his flight due to Deathwing. But Krasus/Korialstraz saved some of his eggs in a separate dimension so Malygos could rebuild his flight later in time.  The reason Malygos and his flight went nuts in WotLK is because of the magic rifts all over Northrend like the Nexus. Same effect the Demon Soul was having on Neltharion.", "creationdate": "2010-07-12T13:11:52-05:00", "id": 172726, "rating": 5, "commentid": 407090, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "600134", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 3, "id": 428957, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "104150", "body": "Kalecgos is another member of the Blue Dragonflight, Malygos was his \"lord\".", "date": "2008-11-02T19:28:33-06:00", "rating": 66, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 4, "id": 456882, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "rufio", "body": "First of all Malygos has a 10min enrage-timer over all phases, so it's important beeing fast at p1 and p2, so you have more time in p3\n\n[u]Here is how we get the magic seeker[/u]\n<unleash> EU-Gorgonnash\n\n[b]Phase 1[/b]\nOne Tank on Malygos, should be well geared. Breath does huge damage (~20k +).\n[u]Sparks[/u] - Range DD should nuke the sparks until 10% or so, let them fly to a good position an kill them, the +50% DPS zone is needed, DK is great in pulling the sparks to melee's \n[u]Tornado[/u] - Priest should spam coh, Druids AE Hots, you can cast instants an sometimes do melee hits. NOTE: after a Tornado Malygos will cast his Breath, wich will kill everyone in front of him (except MT) our MTs runs always after it into the south, the raid in all other directions\nPhase 1 goes to 50% NOTE: if p1 ends keep nuking on Malygos!\n\n[b]Phase 2[/b]\n[u]Adds[/u] - We have 3 Tanks for the melee adds, melees focus them, rogues get on the platforms first and stunning the caster, so you protect your raidmember from beeing focused. Caster just nuke the casters ;) NOTE: as Prot-Warri imp Spellreflect saves lifes\n[u]Zones[/u] - keep moving from zone to zone thats all\nPhase 2 ends when all adds death NOTE: keep nuking Malygos at end of p2!\n\n[b]Phase 3[/b]\nNever go into melee range to Malygos and get out of the coulds asap!\n[u]We build 2 camps[/u], one at the east an one in the south, we always fly left to avoid clouds.\n[u]We used 5 Healers[/u], that means, just hottig around an spamming heal ultimate, so your mates will only die on triple focus from Malygos without the absorbshield!\n[u]The other dragons just dps'n Malygos [/u] the key is stacking the dot asap, a 5cp dot only have an increased duration, not more dmg! So 2cp -> finish, 1cp -> finish, 2cp->finish (or make a 2/3/2 cycle) your dot should stack up to 10+\n\nVery easy fight with this tactic, hf looting and sry 4 my bad english ;)", "date": "2008-11-19T20:01:37-06:00", "rating": 78, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I find the best rotation is to do:  1, 1, 2, 3.  How to do it:  When the fight starts, press 3 repeatedly so you build up your heal stacks on yourself. Malygos won't be targetable for a few seconds so this is a good use of time.  Your rotation will be repeated with a 10 second duration, preferably 8-9 seconds to ensure neither your engulf nor heal stacks drop off. Build 2 combo points with flame spike, hit engulf, then revivify. After your first rotation, only hit engulf when it has about 3 seconds left on its duration, to account for lag and travel time. X-Perl helps here to highlight your ow", "creationdate": "2008-11-19T20:01:38-06:00", "id": 449495, "rating": 11, "commentid": 456882, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "178740", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Warlocks can use http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=48020 to get out of the tornado.  Save your healers some mana and yourself some stress.", "creationdate": "2009-01-11T20:59:49-06:00", "id": 72104, "rating": 26, "commentid": 456882, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "183179", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "my group had 2 Dks for 10 man maly, we got him after a few wipes but with 2 DKs, placing sparks is a cake walk.....death grip and chains of ice them, next spark comes around, DK1s death grip will be on CD but DK2s will be g2g, grip and chain...easy. little tip...if you use a DK and have only one on sparks, let them play with the sparks for a bit before you dps, with a little practice a single DK can place sparks every time to give you double buffs from them", "creationdate": "2009-02-20T05:38:23-06:00", "id": 81283, "rating": 11, "commentid": 456882, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "189601", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "As in, don't know when it got fixed, though, our last 25-man Malygos to burst some adrenaline, our warlocks found out that it is not longer working ability. So you can't use Demonic Circle: Teleport to get out of the vortex.  [url=http://forums.worldofwarcraft.com/thread.html?topicId=16474258213&sid=1]Other conversation on wow-europe forums about this same topic[/url]", "creationdate": "2009-05-22T03:30:19-05:00", "id": 99409, "rating": 8, "commentid": 456882, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Sxeros", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-11-19T20:04:23-06:00", 1, "rufio"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 5, "id": 468054, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "reidsb", "body": "Phase 3 can be practiced with the quest (and unlocked daily) [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=13413]Aces High![/url]", "date": "2008-11-24T21:42:19-06:00", "rating": 74, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 6, "id": 469942, "nreplies": 8, "sticky": 0, "user": "112784", "body": "According to the tome Legacy of the Aspects, written by a human seeking knowledge amongst the night elves, Malygos does not have the form of a \"typical dragon.\" The human author of the book writes that Malygos can change his form \"at will,\" which is, of course, not a unique ability among the dragonflights. Particularly interesting are the words that follow. The human author writes, \"Rarely seen after his retreat to the far north, he is almost always in the form of an insect-like creature, but while in dragon form he, and his flight, are varying blues in color.\" If the account is true, it strongly suggests Malygos lives -- or once lived -- among the Nerubian race of Northrend. \r\n\r\nMalygos has an extraordinary command over magic, and although he is not as powerful physically, his spellcasting more than counters that disadvantage. Malygos lives in a cave within Northrend, and his lair contains many arcane magical artifacts. Malygos and his flight search for any magical source and artifacts and protect them so that mortal races may not endanger the world with their reckless use. He was closest to his brother Neltharion, the Earth Warder, prior to the War of the Ancients. \r\n\r\nWith his flight nearly annihilated, Malygos began to lose his mind. He felt deep guilt for his role in convincing the other Aspects to infuse their powers into the Demon Soul. He traveled to his lair in Northrend, where he hid for millennia. Feelings of remorse paralyzed him. During the ten thousand years following The War of the Ancients, he was rarely seen by the other Aspects. His body was a caricature of his former self. A thin body surrounded by frozen ice, almost skeletal. \r\n\r\nMalygos is the oldest of the five Aspects, possibly the oldest dragon still living.", "date": "2008-11-25T15:53:18-06:00", "rating": 59, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Deathwing, or Neltharion the Earth Warder as he was called before, was on par with the other Dragon Aspects(Malygos the Spell-Weaver, Alexstrasza the Life-Binder, Ysera the Dreamer and Nozdormu the Timeless One), his power was over the earth and ground, presenting the primal force of the world.  They were all in charge of protecting different aspects of the World, Magic, Time, Emerald Dream(dreams), Life and Earth.  Their abilities differed so much that they could not be tested in single combat against each other, they would throw different types of assault and use different ways, shields and ", "creationdate": "2008-11-25T15:53:19-06:00", "id": 380406, "rating": 15, "commentid": 469942, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Drenvion", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "[quote]possibly the oldest dragon still living.[/quote]  Well, not for long :-)", "creationdate": "2008-12-09T12:22:11-06:00", "id": 63297, "rating": 74, "commentid": 469942, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "19191", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "@Blindguard  Nefarian is Neltharion's son, I believe, and Neltharion the Earth Warder (aka Deathwing) is the black dragon aspect, not Nefarian.  I'm fairly certain of this, though I suppose I could be wrong.", "creationdate": "2009-09-12T14:40:20-05:00", "id": 121648, "rating": 9, "commentid": 469942, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "211123", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "@ Debriz  You're not, Nefarian and Onyxia are Neltharion's (Deathwing's) children. Neltharion the Earth Warder was the 5th aspect.", "creationdate": "2010-09-26T18:58:43-05:00", "id": 183863, "rating": 5, "commentid": 469942, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "305281", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Actually Neltharion is the Eldest of the Aspects and is the most powerful and the impromptu leader of them before he went insane", "creationdate": "2011-06-23T14:09:41-05:00", "id": 247637, "rating": 3, "commentid": 469942, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "DrekoArcon", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 7, "id": 476630, "nreplies": 7, "sticky": 0, "user": "94097", "body": "Phase 1 and 2 are pretty much tank and spank ... Phase 3 is a lil bit more of a learning curve. I created these macros for my guildies, and we downed him in 2 attempts once they started using them\r\n\r\nPhase 3 Dragon Macros:\r\n\r\n--- DPS ---\r\n/tar mal\r\n/castsequence reset=target Flame Spike, Flame Spike, Engulf in Flames\r\n\r\n--- Healing ---\r\n/tar pet\r\n/castsequence [target=pet] Revivify, Revivify, Life Burst", "date": "2008-11-28T19:37:38-06:00", "rating": 56, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Can i ask how do u use macroses in P3 in u dont have ur action bars but only dragon contol one?", "creationdate": "2008-12-01T15:21:58-06:00", "id": 365885, "rating": 7, "commentid": 476630, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Maha", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Great macros just one question... how do you use it?  If all you have a is the drake action bar. Do you have to use any special addons if so wich ones?   Please dont down rate me I'm sure a lot people would like to know the answer.", "creationdate": "2009-04-22T03:35:36-05:00", "id": 93066, "rating": 21, "commentid": 476630, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "196175", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Bind the actionbar button to a hot key under options->Key Bindings", "creationdate": "2009-06-15T21:59:50-05:00", "id": 104030, "rating": 8, "commentid": 476630, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "331558", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "What you do is to make the macro, then bind it to a key that you don't use with the mounts other commands.  For example, if you use the keys 1 through 6 for your standard actions, those are what you'll use on a vehicle. If you bind a button on a different actionbar to say shift+1 then put the macro on that action button, you will be able to use it on a vehicle since it won't conflict with your other commands. You can test this out with a macro that just does \"/poke\" on any vehicle (I tried it at the Argent Tournament grounds) just to make sure it's working.", "creationdate": "2009-06-19T14:32:19-05:00", "id": 104699, "rating": 7, "commentid": 476630, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "360094", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "[s]You don't need to /target pet in healing macro, since you already using [target=pet] modifier in it. Because of that, it became much more convenient in watching Maly targets. (Addons that featuring TargetOfTarget and self-aggro notification helps alot in this case)[/s]  Sorry guys, i was wrong. Blizzard should fix their minds regarding mechanics related to combo points and finishing moves. Unless you actually target your victim, you can't spend combo points, when they are accumulated.", "creationdate": "2009-06-28T18:41:48-05:00", "id": 106562, "rating": 7, "commentid": 476630, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "AnrDaemon", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 8, "id": 480414, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Stabb", "body": "A few notes to the fellow rogues out there:\r\n\r\nIf you're combat specced with Killing Spree, save Killing Spree until you're in the vortex! If you cast Killing Spree in vortex you will instantly jump on the boss, and after the attacks are made you will land on the floor, and can dps him / run away from the tank before the others.\r\n\r\nAlso, in phase 2, do NOT use Killing Spree when you're on a Hover Disc, this will remove it, and you'll have to get a new one.", "date": "2008-11-30T13:17:40-06:00", "rating": 42, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I just want to confirm that this comment is 100% true.  Also, if your timing is perfect, you can use Killing Spree right as the vortex starts and completely avoid any damage (assuming you do not take fall damage, so Glyph of Safe Fall is probably another excellent choice for a minor glyph).  Your healers will love you, and if there is any power spark residue below Malygos, you can spend that whole time dealing a ton of damage to him.  Due to the cooldown on Killing Spree, you can only do this every other vortex, but it's still a great way to get through that first phase a little bit easier.", "creationdate": "2009-01-07T08:12:40-06:00", "id": 70898, "rating": 18, "commentid": 480414, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Valustria", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-12-01T09:39:02-06:00", 1, "Stabb"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 9, "id": 482985, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "258545", "body": "You have got to be kidding me. Any1 mind explaining to me how you kill an Aspect?\r\n\r\nSeriously, an Aspect is the representative of all that it standas for. So killing him, destroys all magic in Azeroth = No Mages, No Fire-Locks, no dalaran, no nothing. So, when you are killing him, you are killing mages...\r\n\r\nOn second thought... KILL THE B*STARD! :p", "date": "2008-12-01T15:26:46-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "he was empowered by the titans to guard / control magic, he failed. magic will remain without an aspect.", "creationdate": "2008-12-02T08:31:08-06:00", "id": 366129, "rating": 1, "commentid": 482985, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "pyrokin", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Well It seems to me that it is not so simple. Yes magic has been here far sooner than Malygos but is he dead? You have seen his fall, not his corpse...  It/He is falling through Eye of Eternity... Place without limits, I doubt even Alexstrazsa understands it completly... And even if so... Medivh was also trully dead. He was killed by Khadgar in Karazhan shortly before the first fall of Stormwind. his Mother brought him back. From where and how... Do not think that because you have seen someones defeat you can think him to be dead...  Remember Kael\u00b4thas Sunstrider", "creationdate": "2008-12-03T07:18:37-06:00", "id": 366557, "rating": 2, "commentid": 482985, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "263049", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "A tabard represents a guild.  I'm going to destroy my guild tabard and see if my guild disbands.  ...  Nope. You owe me some silver, buddy.", "creationdate": "2008-12-24T11:29:55-06:00", "id": 374279, "rating": 2, "commentid": 482985, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "182913", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 10, "id": 484419, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "42107", "body": "Exact abilities drakes in phase 3 have:\r\n[ul]\r\n[li][b][url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=56091]Flame Spike[/url][/b][/li]\r\n[li][b][url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=61621]Engulf in Flames[/url][/b][/li]\r\n[li][b][url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=57090]Revivify[/url][/b][/li]\r\n[li][b][url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=57143]Life Burst[/url][/b][/li]\r\n[li][b][url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=57092]Blazing Speed[/url][/b][/li]\r\n[li][b][url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=57108]Flame Shield[/url][/b][/li]\r\n[/ul]", "date": "2008-12-02T07:32:38-06:00", "rating": 65, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "These are the same abilities you use when riding the drakes for Wrymrest daily \"Aces High\". If you did / are doing it, you should be familiar with them.   The related quest page has tips on how to use the abilities.   http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=13413", "creationdate": "2009-01-15T01:45:02-06:00", "id": 72826, "rating": 18, "commentid": 484419, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Nycteris", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 11, "id": 487580, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "242099", "body": "Here is what my guild did for phase 3:\r\n\r\nWe had one person put a mark above their head (preferably something that sticks out like blue square) and that individual flew behind Malygos. Everyone else then clumps up on that person. Assign four dedicated healers, and one confident person who can call out when the lightning charge hits the group (if they angle their camera in the right way you can call it out before it hits the group.) The rest of the raid is on DPS. (For 10 man version have 2 healers instead of 4.)\r\n\r\nHealers: Spam Revivify on yourself until you have 5 charges then hit Life Burst. Never stop this rotation. If all your healers stay alive throughout the fight you can heal through surges and don't even need to use Flame Shield (but it never hurts to use it anyways). \r\n\r\nDPS: Use 3-4 Flame Spikes and then 1 Engulf in Flames (if you are confident you will never let your stack fall if you just use 1-2 Flame Spikes than go ahead and do that. But for simplicity sakes you should have enough time to be getting four Flame Spikes off.) \r\n\r\nWhen Malygos shoots the electrical charge (that does the AoE damage) have someone call out to move. We move left (counterclockwise around Malygos). So everytime we see the charge animation coming at us we call out Left. \r\n\r\nIt is important to always to clump up on the marked target after you move. Failing to do will mean some people won't be getting hit by Life Burst.", "date": "2008-12-03T14:44:53-06:00", "rating": 27, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "We always have our raid members pop Flame Shield anyways, even though you can heal through it. It makes it go alot smoother, and ensures that no one will die if they are popping it when they should. It isn't a big deal in 10-man, but it is very important in 25-man. It'll kill you in about 4-5 Seconds (Quicker if your drake is not topped up) if you don't pop the shield.   Either way, Phase 3 is very easy once your group gets into a rhythm and are using their abilities as efficiently as possible. Like someone else said, we marked one person with a Skull (Some of the marks blend in with the heal ", "creationdate": "2008-12-03T14:44:54-06:00", "id": 379677, "rating": 9, "commentid": 487580, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "296641", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Confusion can arise from such a comment:  [quote]We move left (counterclockwise around Malygos)[/quote]  Comparing left and right to clock-wise and counter-clock-wise is very dangerous. Facing the boss (12), left (W) would be clock-wise. As you are following the proper motion of a clock around him. I have seen this wipe a raid, pick a direction to move and don't refer to a clock.", "creationdate": "2010-05-02T10:46:48-05:00", "id": 161711, "rating": 4, "commentid": 487580, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "254577", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 12, "id": 496626, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "132376", "body": "There is currently a bug with this fight that occurs during the transition from phase 2 to phase 3 and into phase 3. If a player does not deselect and retarget malygos once during this period they will be unable to use the flame shield drake ability that drastically reduces the damage from surge.\n\nThis bug is easily avoidable, just deselect malygos, then reselect him and you're done, it only needs to be done once.\n\n[u][b]***NOTE***[/u] This bug has been resolved. Malygos is no longer targetable during the transition from phase 2 to phase 3, and does not become targetable until shortly after he has finished positioning himself in phase 3.[/b]", "date": "2008-12-07T21:31:03-06:00", "rating": 33, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-01-22T12:42:47-06:00", 1, "132376"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 13, "id": 497739, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Sxeros", "body": "Not straight-on post to the topic, but giving my opinions.\n\nAs now Malygos slain, I can do nothing else but wait with impatience; when will Neltharion, also known as Deathwing, arrive? Many of the greatest lore characters in Warcraft has already revealed theirselves in-game. As the novel the novel Night of the Dragon revealed, Neltharion is resting below Grim Batol. Us, the one's who are in love with Warcraft lore, amongside hungry raiders, hopefully, are waiting for his arrival. With his children, Onyxia and Nefarian slain, he musn't be the most friendliest person, dragon, who will hopefully give more challenge than Malygos. Gogo Dragonflights!\n\nLestuniem of Moonglade", "date": "2008-12-08T11:09:28-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-12-08T11:09:40-06:00", 1, "Sxeros"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 14, "id": 498863, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "fadeaway", "body": "[s][b]Rogues[/b]:  You can break out of his [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=56105]Vortex[/url] ability by using [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=51690]Killing Spree[/url] or [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=36554]Shadowstep[/url] as soon as you get thrown into the air, making it so you don't take any damage from it.\n\n[b]Warlocks[/b]:  Set down a [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=48018]Demonic Circle[/url] near the center before the fight starts and teleport to it when the boss throws you up into [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=56105]Vortex[/url], this will also prevent you from taking damage as well.[/s]\n\nPatch 3.1:  Rogues and Warlocks can no longer break out of Vortex with any of their abilities.  :(", "date": "2008-12-08T22:59:42-06:00", "rating": 39, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Rogues are still able to KS out of vortex.", "creationdate": "2009-06-17T09:57:17-05:00", "id": 104278, "rating": 10, "commentid": 498863, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "troggers", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-04-20T19:54:07-05:00", 1, "fadeaway"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 15, "id": 499436, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Vlad", "body": "Here is a quick guide for everyone who is in a guild with potential to someday go for [npc=28859]:\n\n[ol]\n[li]Go to [npc=26110] [i](33.5 , 34.4)[/i] in Coldarra[/li]\n[li]Obtain the quest [quest=13412][/li]\n[li]Deliver it to [npc=32548] [i](29.5 , 24.8)[/i], she is on top of a platform -you need to fly[/li]\n[li]Get the daily quest [quest=13413] (first time you even get a blue item) and repeat it until \nyou only dream about flying around doing this daily when you sleep![/li]\n[/ol]\n\nThis way you get gold and reputation, and the [acronym=\"the guild members\"]we[/acronym] [b]can do Malygos easier on Phase 3 and hopefully not wipe[/b] once we get there to it...", "date": "2008-12-09T07:11:21-06:00", "rating": 56, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-09-21T18:43:39-05:00", 2, "Vlad"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 16, "id": 507865, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "244938", "body": "Tarctics oh p3:\r\n1-1-2-3-1-1-2-3-1-1-2-3-1-1-2-3....... nonstop (if u cant use 2 cuz its grey, wait for rage and its appears)\r\nwhen u see yellow letters (Malygos targets you): 1-1-4 or just 1-4 if its lack of rage. Anyway 1-4 is enogh when its used in right time when boss's beam HITS you (non when he start cast it). He cast 3 sec spell, then channel you for 4 sec. You must use 4 when he channels. You can use 4 after 2 sec of his channeling with just one combo point and survive withought troubles.\r\n\r\nYou dont need help each other, just avoid big spheres.", "date": "2008-12-13T14:39:33-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This tactic goes down as Malygos targets you twice for big bang..", "creationdate": "2008-12-30T17:23:33-06:00", "id": 376059, "rating": -1, "commentid": 507865, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "38461", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 17, "id": 512643, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "83968", "body": "I'm not sure if it's only me it happens to, but healing this fight on a priest with Spirit of Redemption causes me problems. Every time I die in phase 3, and I turn into the spirit, I die suspended in the air near the portal once it's worn off. I cannot release my spirit, and when I get rezed, I cannot move at all and need to restart my client. It's absolutely ridiculous and annoying. Anyone else get that problem?", "date": "2008-12-15T20:43:55-06:00", "rating": 24, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Yes, this happens to the priests in our raids every time.", "creationdate": "2008-12-16T01:29:57-06:00", "id": 65125, "rating": 11, "commentid": 512643, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "255402", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "/script RepopMe(); will release you.", "creationdate": "2009-01-26T10:11:47-06:00", "id": 75634, "rating": 23, "commentid": 512643, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "18563", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 18, "id": 513469, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "280055", "body": "[b]Phase 3 Rotations[/b]\r\n\r\n[b]DPS[/b]\r\n\r\nFlame Spike\r\nFlame Spike\r\nWait for approximately 85+ Energy\r\nEngulf in Flames\r\nFlame Spike\r\nFlame Spike\r\nEngulf in Flames\r\n\r\nInsert Flame Shield for Engulf in Flames if Targeted for Surge of Power.  \r\n\r\n[b]Healers[/b]\r\n\r\nParty member -X-(Where X is your party member with lowest HP)\r\n\r\nRevivy Member 1\r\nRevivy Member 2\r\nRevivy Member 3\r\nRevivy Member X\r\nWait for 85 Energy\r\nLifeburst Member X\r\nRepeat", "date": "2008-12-16T07:30:51-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": ">>Healers  Party member -X-(Where X is your party member with lowest HP)  Revivy Member 1 Revivy Member 2 Revivy Member 3 Revivy Member X Wait for 85 Energy Lifeburst Member X Repeat <<  Does this ^^ work?  When you spread the hot around like that do you in fact add the combo points to yourself?", "creationdate": "2008-12-16T11:52:51-06:00", "id": 371538, "rating": 0, "commentid": 513469, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "280652", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "No, you lose combopoints when you do stuff to another target. Best practice is just to spam Revivify on your own drake. The AoE healing from Life Burst is enough to keep everyone up if people move/shield properly.", "creationdate": "2008-12-22T09:16:23-06:00", "id": 66832, "rating": 6, "commentid": 513469, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "278973", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "While you do lose combo points if you change targets, there's absolutely nothing wrong with burning the combo points, then targeting another player.  The aoe hot is great, and you'll almost never need to target another player if your raid is excellent, but a 5 stack of the single target heal is amazing for people that aren't protecting themselves quite so perfectly.", "creationdate": "2009-03-06T12:25:31-06:00", "id": 84012, "rating": 1, "commentid": 513469, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Laila", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "What I've found easier to do is to heal whoever has the least HP and hit revivify then pick someone else. If Malygos decides to pick another target, just finish off your combo points and pick someone else instead of wasting the combo points. Some people can't always wait for the life burst to get some heals, give them some hots to keep them going.  A good group will avoid most of the static field damage and you'll only need to focus on keeping up whoever got hit on the power surge.", "creationdate": "2009-03-09T10:27:38-05:00", "id": 84557, "rating": 2, "commentid": 513469, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Raek", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 19, "id": 513846, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "54335", "body": "Here's a few tips if you're trying to beat the enrage timer on this boss.\r\n\r\n1.  If you're running three tanks trying running two tanks instead.  The 25-man version requires you to have four tanked ads meaning that at some point one tank would have to tank at least two ads.  The extra DPS gained means bursting through this encounter easier without meeting the gear requirements.  My guild's first kill almost everyone but me was terribly undergeared, we used one tank (myself) I rounded up all the ads and had people assist off me and watch threat on other ads.\r\n2.  Pre-assign a discs order for P2.  You want to load up as many ranged as possible on this fight but make sure to bring your highest DPS regardless.  In 25-man we have all casters try and DPS the Scions while melee kill the Lords.  Melee go up one at a time in the set order... its a big list.  If you have to choose between a prot warrior going up and a caster you should probably choose the prot warrior the extra sunders added to the scions will help hunters on the groud and melee in the sky.\r\n3.  In phase three have everyone stack on one set location.  I know a lot of strats suggest splitting up groups but if you feel you have 25 competent players they just move right to avoid the AOE dmg, shield themselves from his instagib, and spam their healing/dps buttons.  We use three healers total for this phase freeing up 4 more people to DPS.   If everyone is stacked properly lifeburst heals everyone and there's never a need for any excessive amount of healers.\r\n\r\nIf after this you still can't beat the enrage timer get your lowest dpsers out doing heroics OR look at your debuffs/buffs list and make sure you have them all.", "date": "2008-12-16T11:23:30-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Phase 1: double buffing power sparks really cuts phase 1. We've managed with only 2 tornados being cast. Keep shootinging as he flies away at the end of the phase. With stacked power sparks  you can get him down to 35% - 40%   Phase 2: have deathknights grab some Scions, melee kills the grabbed Scions. Ranged helps with the first 2 Scions, then switches to Nexus lords.  Phase 3: keep the dot stack growing. A dropped stack is futile overall DPS.", "creationdate": "2008-12-19T03:55:16-06:00", "id": 372517, "rating": 0, "commentid": 513846, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "240325", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 20, "id": 527600, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "BuTbKa", "body": "Anybody knows what is event fires when Malygos fixing eyes on me?", "date": "2008-12-24T00:56:02-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 21, "id": 536917, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "carldudut", "body": "ok peeps this is my secret how to heal in malygos as holy paladin! =)\n[b]\nnote: you need [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=41106]Glyph of Holy Light[/url][/b]\n\n[u][b]First Phase[/b][/u]\n\nHeal normal until you got [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=56105]Vortex[/url] for some duration. At this time chuck your [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=53563]Beacon of Light[/url] on the tank then [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=48825]Holy Shock[/url] yourself! If you do it quick enough you could chuck 2x [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=48825]Holy Shock[/url] at that air phase. While wait for your [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=48825]Holy Shock[/url] cooldown which is 6 seconds, target Malygos and chuck [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=20271]Judgement of Light[/url]. After [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=56105]Vortex[/url] finish all of your raid member will be fall in the same spot or aka stack up. At this time as soon as possible use Holy Light on yourself (is compulsory to have [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=41106]Glyph of Holy Light[/url][/b]). Depending on your haste, how many holy light you can use as soon possible before people spread out. Myself can throw 2 Holy Light.\n\n[b][u]Second Phase[/u][/b]\n\nAt this phase I recommended you to chuck yourself [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=53601]Sacred Shield[/url] before change to other orb/bubble/shield half egg or wateva you call it =P, the rest is the same you always do normally as healer. Which is you need to run to other orb/bubble/half egg thingy when it spawn a new one.\n\n[b]Third Phase[u][/u][/b]\n\nThis phase basically focus on using your drake really well. You could do the Wyrmrest Dailies in Coldara which helps a lot on the fight. Usually raid stack up together when this phase come out so when they all on drake, they will be all stack up and you can follow them if you don't know what to do.\n\nI'll share more tips and guide if I could find more =] have a nice day and safe trip for your Malygos fight", "date": "2008-12-29T23:04:50-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2008-12-29T23:05:52-06:00", 1, "carldudut"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 22, "id": 547966, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "asloversgo", "body": "Malygos seems to be the only dragon whose \"wing-skin\" reaches down the tail.\n\nEdit: I stand corrected. Cyanigosa and Azuregos also has it, as Drunkard says!", "date": "2009-01-05T10:20:37-06:00", "rating": 23, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Actually, his blue dragon buddies [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=31134]Cyanigosa[/url] and [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=6109] Azuregos[/url] both have \"wing-skin\" that reaches down the tail.", "creationdate": "2009-04-03T20:03:44-05:00", "id": 89256, "rating": 7, "commentid": 547966, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Drunkard", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Kalecgos also have his ''wing-skin'' that reaches down his tail.", "creationdate": "2012-07-30T06:22:05-05:00", "id": 560391, "rating": 3, "commentid": 547966, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Tyerr", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-09-12T11:16:45-05:00", 1, "asloversgo"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 23, "id": 552615, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "195360", "body": "[u]Tips for 10man Malygos[/u]\r\nThis boss proved a lot more difficult than I believed due to the usual \"he's cakewalk\" comments...\r\n\r\nMy guild wiped for 3 days before finally downing him on the 3rd.\r\n\r\nThis was on 10man. I am told 25man is easier.\r\n\r\nHere's a few suggestions for anyone who might be stuck.\r\n\r\nPhase 1:\r\n\r\n-Hits the MT for 11-9k dmg per swing. Melee swing is slow.\r\n-Arcane Breath brings up a huge damage spike and is the potential tank killer. Let your healers be aware.\r\n-The \"gear requirement\" in this fight is NOT a joke. Even with combined spark buffs, we downed him 5 secs after enrage.\r\n\r\nOur raid setup was: 1 tank (me, 30.6k hp unbuffed prot warrior, all 80 epics except for trinkets), 2 healers (CoH priest and resto druid, both over 2k spellpower and huge mp5), and 7 dps (all tried and tested in other raids, well over 3k constant dps).\r\n\r\nHave the entire raid stack on the very middle of the area, while the tank brings Malygos to the edge of the inner ring, right where the outer ring starts.\r\n\r\nThe tank needs to be completely aware of his surroundings to see where sparks come from. When a spark spawns, he needs to kite Malygos around the edge of the inner ring (just follow the line, it's simple) to position him so that the raid is between him and the spark. Assign a ranged dps to bring the spark to 20%-50% and burst it down when it's on top of the raid.\r\n\r\n2 Sparks will come between each Vortex. One right after and one while you fight.\r\n\r\nWhile the raid is in the Vortex, locate any incoming sparks, and have the tank position Malygos immediatly after everyone lands. If done correctly, the raid just has to run to the center after each votex.\r\n-----------------------------------------\r\nOn phase 2:\r\n\r\nThe tank takes both Nexus Lords. ALL dps nuke these down first. Don't split the dps, as you need to take the Lords out of the fight asap to reduce the raid's damage intake. The only exceptions are the hunters, who should only attack the Scions on the disks if they can't attack the Nexus Lord due to minimum range.\r\n\r\nIf you're a prot warrior, Improved Spell Reflect will save your raid member's life when running from one anti-magic zone to the next, as you will reflect the Scion's spells. Also useful to help out the healers. Use it on EVERY cooldown if possible, time it so you have it available when people run from bubble to bubble.\r\n-----------------------------------------\r\nOn phase 3:\r\n\r\nAll has been pretty much said. Just keep an eye out for the lightning clouds (you'll see Malygos shoot a spark at the grp), stay grouped up, and keep the DoT up.\r\n\r\nPhase 1 is the most difficult to get through, as you have to do itas fast as possible and keep *everyone* alive.\r\n\r\nHope this helped", "date": "2009-01-08T07:00:23-06:00", "rating": 19, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "About healing 10-men version of Maly. You need either druid or priest to heal through vertex phase. Haven't healed as a priest, but as a druid I do the follwing: 1) Check how many people are below 19k hp buffed (please correct me if I am wrong with this number). If none - you can relax, because they won't die even without your heals during vortex. 2) 5-6 seconds before vortex starts, throw lifeblooms on the people with lowest health - last tick will arrive when they are already in the air and took some damage. 3) Right before you go up in the air, do wild growth. Before 3.0.8 I was doing it wh", "creationdate": "2009-01-08T07:00:24-06:00", "id": 382779, "rating": 3, "commentid": 552615, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "219211", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "If your group set-up is not optimum is very hard if the gear is not at least naxx10 level. With a group farming naxx10 we had a very hard time at malygos with 1 coh priest , 2 shamans and no DK. DPS was complaining of having hard time gathering the sparks and for me (the priest) being the only healer healing in the vortex, I tell you I had a hard time. COH heals for 1800-2400 crit with my gear but there are some problems. Sometimes not all 5 charges are spent (some ppl seem to be out of heal range in the vortex) so on average 3-4 ppl are healed by 1 coh. Mending jumps (6 times) but during the ", "creationdate": "2009-01-08T07:00:24-06:00", "id": 379870, "rating": 1, "commentid": 552615, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "90923", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I have to disagree with that gear requirement statement. If you guild is good, executes its well enough, doesn't waste dps, and knows how to do phase 3, then gear doesn't matter as much.", "creationdate": "2009-01-11T18:02:14-06:00", "id": 379690, "rating": 2, "commentid": 552615, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Garysan", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "You are very off, I brought all the most [i]Skilled[/i] dps i knew, but gear will add further to it, the majority of wipes on malygos are poor geared tanks that die too soon, or lack of dps because you have an enrage timer, that comes faster than you think. I know because I tried to heal this fight (holy pally).", "creationdate": "2009-01-27T19:59:58-06:00", "id": 384079, "rating": 3, "commentid": 552615, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "230698", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 24, "id": 553950, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Taleron", "body": "A quick note to Prot Warriors out there, but you may want to watch out for your spell reflect and party reflect skills on this fight in phase 2. It can be really handy, but it could prove dangerous too:\r\n\r\nOn one of our attempts, our MT for the group had party reflect up to protect against the Scions' Arcane Barrage attacks. Unfortunately, I noticed that my SCT popped up a \"Reflect\" message, and... no new bubble landed for us. We had to resort to huddling the whole raid inside a space the size of a shoebox until we got another one.\r\n\r\nMy assumption is that the protection bubble that Malygos fired came close enough that if it landed, it would've triggered the knockback effect that they have when they expand, and that caused the bubble spell to be reflected. It's not a horrible thing as long as you have some kind of bubble to stay in, but if the already existing ones are getting pretty small you could end up in real trouble by having a reflect up at a bad moment.", "date": "2009-01-09T01:10:30-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "To prevent this from occurring, protection warriors should try to wait until a new bubble has formed before hitting spell reflect again.", "creationdate": "2009-01-11T16:22:49-06:00", "id": 72035, "rating": 2, "commentid": 553950, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "1654", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Ideally, you want to be casting it whenever you run in between bubbles, and you usually run between bubbles after a new one has been freshly cast, so you can work up a nice little rhythm as you nervously watch raid HP bars and wait for the disk :P", "creationdate": "2009-01-19T12:11:40-06:00", "id": 73788, "rating": 2, "commentid": 553950, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "90927", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 25, "id": 558198, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "296641", "body": "This might be a little off-topic but i have to add that the animation of the ground splitting was a cool idea on blizzards part, same with the flying discs that the DPS use in the air. \r\n\r\nWhen you get the fight down, it's extremely fun.", "date": "2009-01-11T17:32:55-06:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 26, "id": 559198, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "171643", "body": "killed him yesterday, from a resto druid pov (10-man)\r\n\r\nphase 1 healing is pretty straightforward: \r\nstart putting lifeblooms on raid when he starts the animation for cyclones, u can use instants even during it so its really easy, wildgrowth was hitting only 2 ppl while in air, use it after the raid lands, tank healing is easy too, just make sure he is topped before malygos does its breath\r\n\r\nphase 2 is a bit frustating: \r\nthe problem with phase 2 is the random targeting of the scion of eternity ability, when the raid is changing spot and is vulnerable, if someone is unlucky and get hit 2 times in a very short time he is likely to kiss the floor, it is imperative that u react very fast and keep everyone topped off\r\ninnervate before it starts, u want full mana and u dont need it for phase 3\r\nmake use of Nourish ! i am a big fan of glyphed Regrowth but i learned that during this phase the shorter cast time of Nourish helps a lot\r\nduring power surges wild growth works a blast, when 3.0.8 lands u should preemptively cast lifeblooms as it will have a 6s cooldown, also Tranquillity will negate power surge, keep it for when u want some relief\r\n\r\nphase 3 as others have already said Revivify yourself to 5 and use Life Burst, its easy enough and effective\r\n\r\nhope it helps", "date": "2009-01-12T09:19:52-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 27, "id": 560380, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "148878", "body": "After about 3 hours of wipeing, we finally killed him last night. In phase 2 we kept the melee dps to kill the mobs on the ground, while the ranged dps took the disks and killed the ranged mobs.", "date": "2009-01-13T02:57:08-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 28, "id": 560777, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "18147", "body": "Yes, scroll up. No info on how to avoid it yet other then not die.  GL", "date": "2009-01-13T09:34:29-06:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "10 man EoE = Easy mode.   In 25 man EoE the Tank and Raid takes alot More DMG!   On top of that you have to get 25 raiders working together perfectly instead of 10.     During Phase 1 a fully Geared Tank will be taking almost 27k of DMG every 2-3 seconds.  If the boss eats a spark your looking at a 34k+ hit to the tank.   Better bring out the big gun healers because a pallys 18K heals are golden to keep the tank up.   We use 2 Pallies on the TANK and 2 Priests, Shammy and a Druid on the Raid.  A few tricks to make your lives easier on 25 man.    Have Healin Pallies Spec 17 pts into Protection ", "creationdate": "2009-01-13T09:34:30-06:00", "id": 380173, "rating": 3, "commentid": 560777, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "264218", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Ouch... thats all I'm saying... just ouch.  But on the bright side, the healadin pally idea is great, and druids stacking hots before vortex is great aswell. And if you dont want guardian spirit to bug? Go disc, penance can be cast in vortex :D", "creationdate": "2009-01-17T02:42:13-06:00", "id": 73236, "rating": 3, "commentid": 560777, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "291866", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Thanks for the tip about the strafe. We have been farming him only to go tonight and have our healers both get insta-gibbed on separate attempts. Was bad luck no doubt, but will def be trying the strafe trick next attempt.", "creationdate": "2009-01-19T12:13:55-06:00", "id": 73789, "rating": 3, "commentid": 560777, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "90927", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 29, "id": 568691, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "260974", "body": "Hunters might want to sit out for this fight. I've had nothing but trouble in the repeated attempts at this fight. During repeated clears of Naxx10 and other raid content in LK, I've almost always been 1st or 2nd dps, but Malygos really requires close quarters dps, which a hunter isn't capable of providing. Coupled with the fact that hunter pets have a bad habit of glitching after the first vortex, you become almost useless as far as DPS is concerned. Keeping yourself in range for sparks is equally as hard because of its rather large hit box. \r\n\r\nBasically, if you're a hunter, you better hope the rest of your raid can make up for your severely stunted dps.  \r\n\r\nHopefully blizz realizes that pets glitch and the spark radius is crap and hunters get a bit of a help out here sometime.", "date": "2009-01-18T23:10:27-06:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "To prevent pet glitching:   When you land after the vortex phase, click Passive on your pet action bar.  Then, when you're ready to attack, use a /petattack macro (or just hit Ctrl-1).  Since doing this I've never had a problem with my pet bugging out.", "creationdate": "2009-01-25T16:48:02-06:00", "id": 75458, "rating": 6, "commentid": 568691, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Pazhala", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 30, "id": 569460, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "90927", "body": "Think I was quite thorough with the comments above, and couldn't see anything on this. Has anyone encountered difficulties on using your fire shield? On two separate encounters I remember that it did not activate despite having at least 2-3 combo points and Malygos targeted. At first I thought I had too little energy, but the 2nd time I made sure I had enough. Has anyone else come across this?", "date": "2009-01-19T12:36:16-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 31, "id": 570229, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "137927", "body": "First to people who have trouble with the fire shield:\nIf you target Malygos during the transition from Phase 2 to Phase 3 you must untarget him once you get on your drake or Fire Shield will not cast. Not sure if that's being fixed in the next patch or not, but it's an easy enough thing to get by.\n\nSecond to the locks doing this raid:\nYou can use your Teleport, rogues can use Killing Spree and Shadowstep *I think those are there two,* to get out of the vortex and avoid taking damage. \nAlso, during the transition from Phase 2 to 3 make sure to cast Curse of the Elements on Malygos. It's the only thing that will last the entire fight and adds 10%, 13% if specced, more damage for everyone. Once you get those 15 stacks up and you're doing 28k ticks you'll be glad it's up. :-)\n\nEdit: One last thing for casters. If all of the Melee have a disk and there's still extra disks left over in Phase 2, feel free to get on one. You can cast while moving around and avoid the breath. :-)", "date": "2009-01-19T23:35:24-06:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-01-19T23:37:00-06:00", 1, "137927"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 32, "id": 573224, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Mahtamori", "body": "I hate giving second hand information, but apparently the encounter has been changed to prevent multiple sparks, possibly even increasing the range at which the sparks are swallowed. The change has also lead to an increase in the timer in the associated achievement, so that it's more doable.\r\nI'm writing this on patch day (eu), so feel free to down-rate my post and confirm whether this is accurate or not.", "date": "2009-01-21T12:33:44-06:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 33, "id": 574436, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "230934", "body": "dunno if i have to lower my graphics or something but at phase3 the whole room is brightly coloured like petrol on concrete around me and every video i saw was pitch black...my eyes start to bleed ffs and can't see the lightning clouds clear enough :/..can anyone help on that?", "date": "2009-01-22T08:53:59-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 34, "id": 575228, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "TheSteelPhantom", "body": "As of 3.0.8, you can no longer place [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=47865]Curse of Elements[/url] on Malygos at the beginning of Phase 3 (when the platform breaks and knocks you upward a bit). So for anyone who used to do this... well, you can't anymore. Malygos is not targettable in Phase 3 until after the red drakes catch you and he's done with his Yell emote.", "date": "2009-01-22T19:56:42-06:00", "rating": 18, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "You still can put curse of elements on Malygos in phase 3, you just need to sacrifice lock (he jumps off the dragon, throws curse while flying by Maly and then kisses ground). If other 24 raid members stay alive, that will give a very nice boost to dps (which can be useful for 6 minutes achievement).", "creationdate": "2009-02-22T21:34:54-06:00", "id": 81877, "rating": 6, "commentid": 575228, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "219211", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 35, "id": 578977, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Martacus", "body": "FOR ALL YOU OLD SCHOOL PLAYERS AND LORE LOVERS OUT THERE.\r\n(old school being able to remeber when stratholme was a 10 man instance or when arcane explotion used to have a casting time!)\r\n\r\nIt may just be me or does anyone agree with me that Malygos is totaly lacking originailty and the old school raiding spirit? I meen comon guys, think back to Blackwing Lair and AQ 40 ect. How does Malygos compare to bosses Pre- TBC? Would you not rather be dodging C'thuns Eye beam lazas than doing a Boss Which has the same moves as a Daily qest mob? And dont you miss the time when you had to actualy get off your ass and do something to get some epixs. not just /2 LFG Naxx 10 man! or nolifing all day in heroics saving up badges to trade in. Now its allways gear before skills, cos half the bosses post TBC dont require any require any of the skill that was a nescesaty back in the days of 40 man raids.GIEF MOLTEN CORE IN FULL 52 BLUES AGAIN PLZ!\r\n\r\nAND. for all you lore lovers out there (like me) , did'nt you share the dissapointment, knowing that malygos, Aspect of magic and a highly decorated character in the lore, could only spin the raid around, summon mages to do his work, and shoot a few beams wich are absorbed by a dragon wich he would have killed in an instant in the books and lore? or how simple it is to just /LFG and kill Malygos. Surly, blizzard, you can think of  a more exciting,memorable fight for one of the 5 dragon aspects!\r\nI meen , look at kalecgos in the sunwell for instance. Malygos is his Ruler and yet, kalecgos has a far more complicated stratagy, and I for one loved fighting him and  killing that bastard of a deamon in him!\r\n\r\nSo , is there anyone else out there who misses the pre TBC days ? :< \r\nOr have we all sunk into Welfare loot, PuG raids and ...Dailies.\r\n\r\nP.S and PLEASE dont downrate this comment if you have never had the joy of being in a 40 man raid or if you dont give a #$%^ about warcraft lore. let others have theyr say!\r\n\r\nMartacus out! /mourn old school!", "date": "2009-01-24T19:42:01-06:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2009-01-24T19:45:04-06:00", 1, "Martacus"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 36, "id": 579955, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "223121", "body": "Tip for Death Knights here\r\n\r\nAlways pop Anti-magic shell when you're sucked up in Vortex. Not only will this negate a MASSIVE chunk of damage for your healers it will supply you with mass amounts of Runic Power. Not sure on the exact numbers, but I think I was able to throw out a Death Coil every tick of Vortex which, in a DPS race boss, is pretty good.\r\n\r\nSo I guesss this message is basically saying \"Know your class abilities!\" :)", "date": "2009-01-25T10:28:03-06:00", "rating": 32, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 37, "id": 580939, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "kenn213", "body": "Just a quick note for people having issues post 3.0.8:  If your raid keeps dying for no aparent reason there is a bug with pets getting the debuff and hitting the raid. Try dismissing all pets, worked tonight for my guild after a few unexplained wipes.", "date": "2009-01-25T22:01:41-06:00", "rating": 13, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 38, "id": 580952, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "255841", "body": "The guild my friend is in has a strange strategy for Phase 1.  I've tried to convince him that it is purely luck that it works, but I'd like confirmation on that.\r\n\r\nThey say, standing in a spark will prevent you from getting hit by his Arcane Breath.\r\n\r\nI'm 100% sure that i've taken damage from it while on the spark, but he says that he never has.  This isn't something I'd like to actually test.  So hopefully, somebody could clear this up for me.\r\n\r\nThanks.", "date": "2009-01-25T22:10:12-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 39, "id": 581091, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "308293", "body": "I agree with kenn123 . We had same issue , pets took the debuff and they had kill the raid . even if you control them and make them follow you after landing cant stop them from wiping the raid . dismiss them and use them in phase 2 , Unfortunately this is a bug for sure", "date": "2009-01-26T00:51:33-06:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Anyone else feels bad killing this old chap and his misfortunate brood? :(", "creationdate": "2009-01-26T10:01:08-06:00", "id": 383656, "rating": 1, "commentid": 581091, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Grishie", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 40, "id": 585104, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "57891", "body": "You cannot use Circle of Healing in the Vortex anymore since 3.0.8, or any non-instant heals at all for that matter. Made Malygos alot harder.", "date": "2009-01-28T12:44:16-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "You can't use Wild Growth in the Vortex either, but apparently it's a bug. Hopefully it gets fixed because it definitely makes it harder.", "creationdate": "2009-01-29T02:16:31-06:00", "id": 76325, "rating": 3, "commentid": 585104, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "indisposed", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 41, "id": 590099, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "290374", "body": "Why does Malygos sound like a Blood Elf?  >.>  When I imagine badass dragon, I imagine the opposite of Blood Elf voice.", "date": "2009-01-31T22:46:51-06:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Because Malygos' voice actor is Cam Clarke, the same guy who does the Belf-Male-Player voices.  Besides, look at how many dragons disguise themselves as elves, how can you imagine them differently? :p", "creationdate": "2009-07-26T12:10:42-05:00", "id": 111918, "rating": 4, "commentid": 590099, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "vargus", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "/cough /cough [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=33535]Malygos[/url]", "creationdate": "2010-01-17T02:06:54-06:00", "id": 143709, "rating": 2, "commentid": 590099, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "346361", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 42, "id": 591083, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "coolfox", "body": "for phase 3 our guild runs a every man for himself kinda thing, in which u keep ur own health up and u dps the boss, so exactley the same as the aces high quest/daily and it works really well altho its only 10 man we've been able to clear him on cant quite get to phase 3 fast enuff atm, if any 1 would like to try every man for himself on 25 to see if it works and then tell me it would be appreciated", "date": "2009-02-01T15:09:15-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Problem with every man for himself is that you either take forever to build up stacks or you loose all your stacks once you are targeted by Maly. Not to mention that if you get targeted twice, you will most likely die and are guaranteed to not keep stacks up. With 1-2 dedicated healers and everybody else just concentrating on dps, nobody should be loosing stacks of debuff being targeted once and if you are smart, you can keep stacks up even when you have been targeted twice.", "creationdate": "2009-02-22T21:40:30-06:00", "id": 81878, "rating": 1, "commentid": 591083, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "219211", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 43, "id": 596424, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Keranna", "body": "Pets no longer seem to be bugged during vortex - I've noticed that mine despawns when we're all up in the air, and then comes back out right as I land. No issues with him sticking anymore, which is great.\r\n\r\nAnd CoH/WG  not being castable in the Vortex has been confirmed as a bug.\r\n\r\n\r\nWe identified a bug preventing Circle of Healing and Wild Growth from being able to find targets in Vortex. It was not our intent that these heals be prevented during Vortex (beyond the nerf we already made to prevent them from being spammed).\r\n\r\nWe should be able to fix this in the next couple of days.\r\n\r\nhttp://blue.mmo-champion.com/27/14697634915-vortex-damage.html", "date": "2009-02-05T09:22:09-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
