{"commentv2": 1, "number": 63, "id": 733733, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Nycteris", "body": "Hunters can track the sparks with their Track Elemental (http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=19880) spell on their mini maps and then click the map to let the raid know of sparks' locations.", "date": "2009-06-01T02:01:53-05:00", "rating": 14, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 64, "id": 740643, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "aminalbloon", "body": "Recently did Malygos this week, and we usually use /follow on a marked person in phase 3, but it seemed to keep on breaking off for most of us. Have they changed it in the recent patch to make it so that /follow doesn't work anymore or something?", "date": "2009-06-08T09:31:01-05:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I think they've done multiple changes. Our guild used to have no problem with the fight, yet the vortexes seem to be doing massive amounts more damage than they used to.   We would start the vortex with everyone at full then lose 7 people before it ends - and all have over 16k health.   In phase 2, the flying mages seem to focus fire on single targets much more, resulting in deaths that are harder to prevent. And then, as you said, in phase 3 the autofollow doesn't seem to have any range at all.   Blizzard has done some serious damage to this raid. They should at least write it in patch notes ", "creationdate": "2009-06-08T09:31:02-05:00", "id": 410764, "rating": 0, "commentid": 740643, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "AuronFtw", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 65, "id": 754173, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "starsword", "body": "From the 3.2 PTR Patch Notes:\r\n[quote]The Nexus: The Oculus & The Eye of Eternity\r\n\r\n    * Vehicles (drakes) used in these instances now scale with item level.\r\n[/quote]\r\n\r\nFinally, a step in the right direction for those of higher gear levels in finishing this encounter. This should make phase 3 Malygos much more convenient.", "date": "2009-06-21T19:08:18-05:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Addons like [url=http://www.wowinterface.com/downloads/info14286-FLOPFlameLeviathanOPtimizer.html#info]FLOP[/url] will automatically equip your highest-level gear so as to maximize your damage and health.", "creationdate": "2009-08-13T18:28:52-05:00", "id": 115939, "rating": 2, "commentid": 754173, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Corveroth", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
