{"commentv2": 1, "number": 74, "id": 914548, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "358770", "body": "The Dragon Aspects don't have it easy. One goes insane and helps the legion, and the other one needs to be killed for some reason. Over some thousand years probably all the aspects are insane and/or dead. That would mean that all the dragonflights will try to destroy the world. That is gonna be fun", "date": "2009-12-12T06:49:46-06:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 75, "id": 945893, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "178494", "body": "Don't know why, but I've never seen any helpful macros for phase 3 of Malygos encounter. Maybe I have some weird interface/keybind setup, but casting shield on your own drake while moving can be a real pain, so providing that you're using some action bar addon you can setup an easy macro \"/cast [target=pet] Flame Shield\". That way you will never have to change target from Malygos. With the simple 1-1-2-3 rotation and that macro I went from dying upon second focus to top damage done every or almost every time I did the encounter so far.", "date": "2010-01-12T19:19:05-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "If you are targeting Malygos, and have not configured your UI in some outlandish fashion, casting Flame Shield will buff your own Drake. There is no need for a Macro.", "creationdate": "2010-03-16T01:23:57-05:00", "id": 154184, "rating": 3, "commentid": 945893, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "joequincy", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Probably this is true (haven't done EoE for long), but if you target Malygos and want to use the shield, you need to have combo points on him.  However, if you put two stacks of healing on yourself and want to use those combo points for the shield, you need to target your drake. With this macro you don't need to do that. Last time I was in EoE (and before I actually started using any sort of action bar addon), I had to change target every time I wanted to use shield with combo points that are already on my drake.", "creationdate": "2010-09-07T07:31:18-05:00", "id": 180845, "rating": 0, "commentid": 945893, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "178494", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
