{"commentv2": 1, "number": 77, "id": 1013233, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "321140", "body": "Hmm... Wonder what they mean by the fact that Alexstrasza's Gift has been opened 14502 times?", "date": "2010-04-05T15:16:07-05:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Obviously you kill her \"brother\", enter the \"gift\", and come back out with lootz. Double win?", "creationdate": "2010-08-30T15:21:08-05:00", "id": 457701, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1013233, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "561831", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 78, "id": 1045533, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "258919", "body": "Even with people pulling under 3k DPS (and a couple people pulling well above that), the first two stages are cake in a 10-man raid. The only real worries are staying behind Malygos, killing the orbs and using their buffs for ranged DPSers (a DK helps a ton; grip+chains), and staying in the bubbles unless you're riding a disc.\r\n\r\nThe third stage, on the other hand, is more difficult. All of the healers should spam 333334. All of the DPS should spam 112 or 1112. However, classes must watch their energy conservation to make sure they have enough energy to pull off a shield, especially in 10m where there are fewer targets. All drakes  must remain stacked and, when someone is targeted, the group should move left of that person until they are out of range of the AoE. The person who is targeted (DBM covers telling you who it is) should immediately build up 2 combo points and cast the shield. For 10m, we found it best to have a DPSer heal whilst on the drake.\r\n\r\nBasically, phase 3 is passable by moving left (or right, left is what we chose) when someone is zapped, and spamming the above cycles. We managed to down him with about 7 out of 10 people still alive in the end.", "date": "2010-05-24T21:51:52-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 79, "id": 1051375, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Darkomicron", "body": "I'd like to try and clarify this.\nAs the poster above stated correctly, each dragon was imbued by powers of a certain titan, They were later known as: Malygos the Spell-Weaver, Alexstrasza the Life-Binder, Ysera the Dreamer, Neltharion the Earth Warder and Nozdormu the Timeless One.\nThese 5 dragon aspects of each flight (blue, red, green, black and bronze, respectively with the order of the aspects named above) were the mightiest of their kind. Dragons are very 'close' so to say, they call each other brother and sister because they are equal to each other. Another term dragons might use is 'my brood'. This implies more than just a bond between two dragons, they actually have to be brother and/or sister as we use it, of the same clutch. (this is also shown in the War of the Ancients Trilogy)\n\nIf you want to know how Malygos became a prime evil, instead of one of the guardians of the world, read on.\n[i][b]\n[u]**SPOILER IF YOU READ ON**[/u] [/b]\n(War of the Ancients Trilogy)\n.\n\n\n.\n\n\n\n.\n\n\n.\nIn the World of Warcraft - War of the Ancients book series, you learn how Malygos became insane. In short, Neltharion got corrupted by a great evil (supposedly the Old Gods) he created 'the dragon soul' which later became known as the demon soul. The purpose of this Dragon Soul was to decimate the demonic army razing over Azeroth (This was at the time of the first invasion of the burning legion). Every dragon contributed his or her part into the Dragon Soul. However, the dragons didn't expect so see one of their mightiest turn on them, and Neltharion  used the Dragon Soul to attack the races of Azeroth, trying to defend their home. Then he attacked the dragons with it. When he got distracted by an attack of a lonely dragon the blue dragon flight broke loose of his bounds and tried to contain Neltharion (later known as Deathwing (He'll be the new Cataclysm boss)) Neltharion, using the Demon Soul, decimated the Blue flight, and threw Malygos far over the horizon. Malygos became insane  after seeing his flight decimated, it would take decennia to restore the blue dragon flight to it's former glory.\n\n\nEdit: poster below (Mealstrom) might also spoil War of the Ancients lore in his post", "date": "2010-06-03T10:11:23-05:00", "rating": 17, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2010-07-19T09:32:25-05:00", 4, "Darkomicron"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 80, "id": 1053683, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "115110", "body": "In my opinion it was stupid that they killed off Malygos, should have just had him brought back to reality and redeemed. Next expansion will see the return of Deathwing, and Malygos was Deathwing's closest friend before the pair of them went mad, would have been highly relevant to have Malygos participate in the battle against Deathwing.", "date": "2010-06-06T23:18:13-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I think we'll probably find out that there is some massive pot (hopefully) from blizzard, as regards where all the lore with the dragon flights is going...  Deathwing... Corrupted  Nozdormu... believed to be behind the Infinte dragonflight (a lot of evidence pointing towards this)  Ysera... Battle the corruption in the emerald dream and apparently losing (Corrupted dragons invading azeroth via trees)   Malygos... dead  Only Alexstraza seems untouched thus far...  anyway these were the wardens put in charge of watching and safe guarding azeroth when the Titans left and they are falling or seem ", "creationdate": "2010-06-06T23:18:14-05:00", "id": 455318, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1053683, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "484852", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Entirely possible.   But Ysera and deathwing's corruptons both stem from the old Gods. So its unlikely that  Alexstrasza has anything to do with it. Of course she could be corrupted by the old gods as well(or another sinister force) and is as you said just biding her time.  Malygos' madness stems from losing nearly his entire flight(many of which had to be his own kids) at none other than deathwing, his own brother. Not only that but he was the one that convinced the other aspects to give power to the dragon soul. So Neltharion's betrayal is so much worse to him, no wonder he went insane.  sin", "creationdate": "2010-06-06T23:18:14-05:00", "id": 492610, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1053683, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Grabovsky", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
