{"commentv2": 1, "number": 85, "id": 1275906, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Supahtoons", "body": "Anyone have a clue as to if the drakes have a cap on the item level scaling? I'm wondering if Cata gear makes this even easier than it was.", "date": "2011-01-03T21:13:01-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 86, "id": 1330265, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "citrique", "body": "There doesn't appear to be a discernable cap on item level scaling, my drake had about 320,000 HP today in all-359 + some 372 items.\n\nFor what it's worth, Malygos 10-man will be soloable by a DK within a tier or two of gear. I was able to solo him all the way to phase 3, but hit enrage just as phase 3 started. With some better gear and a bit more optimal play with sparks it should be possible to get into phase 3 with about 2 minutes left, enough to kill him.\n\nThe fight is -extremely- difficult to solo to that point though. You must get every single spark in order to do enough DPS to get out of phase 1 in a timely manner. A DK is the only class that can adequately do this. The incoming arcane damage in phase 1 can be heavily mitigated through prismatic elixir, tol barad trinket and anti-magic shell.\n\nPhase 2 is the most difficult part. The Nexus Lords don't hit terribly hard and are easily downed, however the Scion adds will kill you very quickly once you're on a disc and outside the protective shields. I was able to kill all 4 adds only by using every single available defensive cooldown I had and it took several attempts, the incoming damage is upwards of 30-40K/second without cooldowns as you get out from under the shield and the first two adds must be burned down quickly before you run out of cooldowns and are unable to outheal the incoming damage. You also cannot summon/sacrifice a ghoul while on a disc as pet summons do not work.\n\nIn phase 3 a self-sustain rotation (1 1 2 3) should probably be sufficient to survive all incoming damage with high enough ilevel from gear, and will build up 20 stacks reliably. Assuming you can make it into phase 3 with roughly 2.5-3 minutes remaining you should be able to down him solo.", "date": "2011-02-10T10:39:49-06:00", "rating": 13, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Actually he has already been soloed by a Hunter", "creationdate": "2011-02-22T13:54:56-06:00", "id": 227438, "rating": 5, "commentid": 1330265, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "674828", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I am just jumping in the solo bandwagon on my DK.  What kind of gear and spec did you have?  When I tried solo'd most of AQ40 I just ran in with my DPS gear and Blood.", "creationdate": "2011-03-14T15:19:43-05:00", "id": 232223, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1330265, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Ishtar", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "You got very lucky then because after 3 attempts I was able to kill 1 spark. The rest of the time I would run over to kill the spark and, of course, it would hit malygos and he would get the buff. This fight isn't worth the trouble. It was annoying when I did it back in WotLK with 10 people it's even more annoying now.   I hate, no, despise vehicle fights; every single one of them. From Oculus to EoE to Flame leviathan they are all lame. I want to play my class not learn how to play a new class just to do 1 fight.", "creationdate": "2011-03-14T23:25:34-05:00", "id": 481460, "rating": -1, "commentid": 1330265, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Morbius", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Phase 3 is not doable yet, probably need more 372 gear.  I did some research and figured it out - it's been done by a hunter, but there is only one reason why - a hunter who stacked two sparks in the phase 1 to 2 transition and blew all offensive cooldowns to get the boss down to 20% before he flies off, so that he starts phase 3 with low enough HP for him to kill the boss in the roughly 70 second window you have before your drake dies from the incoming damage. A DK can't do this as you can't shave more than about 5% of the boss's HP off in the air with icy touch and death coil.", "creationdate": "2011-03-15T05:37:30-05:00", "id": 232334, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1330265, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "citrique", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-08-28T22:38:08-05:00", 1, "citrique"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 87, "id": 1357832, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "citrique", "body": "Amusing tidbit I discovered in soloing attempts:\r\n\r\nIf you hit berserk in phase 2, the scion adds don't appear to berserk correctly. They gain the 900% damage buff, but it doesn't actually seem to work, they still hit for the same amount.\r\n\r\nSo just for fun, I left one add alive and sat through the entire berserk buff till it fell off, bandaging/rune tap healing, and then did phase 3 normally, though I died at about 20% after hitting the wrong key by mistake and dropping my stack.\r\n\r\nWhile I can hardly recommend anyone use this method to bypass the enrage timer, it does technically work.", "date": "2011-03-05T00:42:50-06:00", "rating": 27, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Totally works, excellent tip. Been trying to find a group to do this with for many months and finally found and tried this. Takes a while (30 mins) for the berserk buff to wear off but totally easier than trying to pug this. Thanks :)", "creationdate": "2013-04-21T23:37:05-05:00", "id": 652836, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1357832, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "bobbigmac", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 88, "id": 1406316, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "HelloKitty", "body": "I had considered this as well. Not only that, but look at who appears to be spearheading all of the attacks?\r\n\r\nMalygos's \"fall\" seemed rather contrived. He was an ancient hero and I feel as though we didn't do him much justice in slaying him. If anything, he seemed rather convinced that he was doing Azeroth good, and we gave him little time to explain. His choppy lore can be tossed up with Illidan as \"righteous slaughter\" without so much merit, honestly. \"Madness\" was just pretty much tossed in with both characters.\r\n\r\nAlexstrasza was the key figure in attacking Malygos, and now the same with Deathwing. I mean, of course, Deathwing has had previous attacks on the dragonflight and his 'cataclysm' debut certainly isn't painting a very innocent picture. Additionally, even back in the BWL days the black dragonflight was all-around pretty gruesome.\r\n\r\nBut it's been a suspicion of mine now, for a long time, that Alexstrasza is a key figure in killing the other dragons. Think about it - she spearheaded the slaying of Malygos, and now she is opportunistically spearheading the assault against Deathwing. What happens next expansion?\r\n\r\nThe Emerald Dream is a likely next target. What can we do there? The most obvious choice is to rid it of 'corruption.' I'm noticing a trend - maybe Deathwing is actually evil - but Malygos seems to have just \"gone mad,\" while the emerald dream is just suffering from \"corruption,\" and the infinite dragonflight are led by no apparent leader other than the suspected Nozdormu.\r\n\r\nCould it be, perhaps, that Alexstrasza is pulling all the strings, here? Maybe she is, in fact, out to kill all of the other dragons, and manipulating the \"heroes\" into doing her bidding for her? Deathwing was dormant for a long time after his lack unsuccessful attempt on Alexstrasza's life, so maybe she just couldn't get to him sooner. Now that she can, she'll take her opportunity.\r\n\r\nWhat if she is the one organizing the corruption in the emerald dream, and will later tell players to slay Ysera under some bull!@#$ notion that Ysera is now 'corrupted' as well?\r\n\r\nAnd, finally, what if she is possibly manipulating the infinite dragonflight (Or, perhaps, influencing Nozdormu to lead it), only to later point the finger at Nozdormu and say HE was the one pulling the strings, telling us to slay him?\r\n\r\nAnd, after that - once we've slain 4/5 of the dragon aspects in over the next 2 expansions (leaving us at lv95) - she announces that her plans are complete, that she actually planned for us to kill the other 4 dragonflight aspects so she could be the sole ruler of all dragonkin? Of course, this is just a hunch, but after our acknowledging her betrayal, we might then launch an attack against her, killing her at lv100, marking the end of the WoW franchise as all 5 dragon aspects are defeated, finally opening the door for WoW2: 100(ish) years down the line, after the 5 dragon aspects are dead, where the world goes, how the Horde/Alliance might split up, etc. etc.\r\n\r\nEntirely speculation, but I wouldn't put it past Blizzard to think that far ahead and consider the various possibilities, especially judging by how shady the Malygos kill was.", "date": "2011-05-01T13:39:42-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Seeing as the dragon aspects have spent their power to defeat Deathwing and are now mortal your conspiracy theory does not work.", "creationdate": "2012-01-27T12:35:27-06:00", "id": 513010, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1406316, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "singularity", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 89, "id": 1414204, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "TehFacroller2000", "body": "This has to be the trippiest encounter ever.", "date": "2011-05-09T18:51:33-05:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 90, "id": 1426078, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "821468", "body": "Thanks to the posts here, i killed Malygos (10) solo today (as a Hunter)\r\n\r\nThe fight ist really tricky, i used an 7/31/3 specc with Spirit Bonds (cause i had to kill Saphiron first, to get the key). Pet Heal und MD Glyph,\r\n\r\nP1: Quite easy.\r\nKeep the pet up und try to kill the sparks to get the Dmgbuffzones. \r\nAfter  every Vortex i got aggro, so i had to use Feign Death. Problem: the pet ist somtimes low on health like after dismounting. Ruined several attempts. \r\nYour goal is to get him down to atleast 40% before P2 starts. Dmg stop right before an Vortex or 2 stacking dmgbuffzones are very helpful (use Rapidfire)\r\n\r\nP2: Really tough.\r\nYou get 7500 dmg per bolt by the Scions, but, as not bosslevel, they miss a lot. Allways stay in the shildzones und bringt the adds down as fast as possible. I noticed; the Scions stop attacking you for a while, after using Feign Death. Looks buggie, but helped a lot.\r\n\r\nP3: Dmg race.\r\nI used the 1,1,2,3  rota stated above and stacked 5 hot stacks before Malygos was attackable again. Avoid the Static Fields before they even hit you once and you should be able to kill him.\r\nI used no other ability und i hardly downed him. I had roughly 20k left as he died. Startet at ~40% in P3.\r\n\r\nImportant: The Dragon in P3 scales with your Itemlevel. With my equip (50/50 359/372) i had 322k hp. With weaker gear you should reset after a weak P1 (40%+).\r\n\r\nI was extremely lucky and got the Reins of the Azure Drake in this first run. Besides the Achievement \"a poke in the eye\" for killing him with less than 9 Player (obviously).\r\n\r\nGood luck to everyone out there and happy farming.\r\n\r\nPlease excuse mistakes in the English language...", "date": "2011-05-24T07:53:54-05:00", "rating": 33, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 91, "id": 1427254, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Crazyrussian", "body": "Just 10manned 25 version in a pug. P3 is where people start dying, what you do is as soon as you get mounted, spam 3 (the heal) up to 5 stacks, when Maly becomes attackable do the rotation 1123 the entire fight and stay out of stuff, easy.", "date": "2011-05-25T13:14:31-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 92, "id": 1434868, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "297533", "body": "155 comments and nobody posted how much gold he drops, its 267 gold on 25man.\r\nCan easily kill with 3-4 people who know what to do, happy mount farming.", "date": "2011-06-05T12:26:50-05:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 93, "id": 1447690, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "remikskr", "body": "With the release of 4.2 Patch you no longer need a key to start Malygos encounter.", "date": "2011-06-22T06:41:07-05:00", "rating": 32, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 94, "id": 1475674, "nreplies": 5, "sticky": 0, "user": "citrique", "body": "As I figured, this is now soloable on 10-man by a blood DK.\n\nhttp://i.imgur.com/RGskD.jpg\n\nI used a 32/0/9 blood DPS spec and glyphs (rune strike) without rune tap and DPS gear. I reforged for 8% hit, had 39 expertise and 9 mastery (as little as possible) with haste/crit stacking. This boss is -barely- doable in this level of gear however, my equipped ilevel is 377. The only reason it is now doable is the death strike damage buff, which makes phase 1 go much more quickly.\n\nTo do this boss: Pull with army. AMS the breath as often as possible. Pop ghoul early (more or less useless damage as the sparks don't affect it). You'll have another ghoul to sac in P2. After the first vortex, kill the first spark before it reaches him, then grip the next spark on top of the aura from the first and kill it, same as you would have done when this boss was current content. Blow DPS cooldowns (DRW, engi gloves, on-use trinkets), burn boss, repeat.\n\nPhase 2 is the difficult part. Have a ghoul out to sac (you can not summon one while on a disc). Kill the first Nexus Lord, leave the second one alive on the ground. Fly up, AMS and burn one nether scion down, then drop down into a magic suppression zone and VB/DS heal up off the still alive Nexus Lord, killing it. Ghoul sac. Fly back up, IBF and kill the remaining scions as quickly as possible before you get overwhelmed by their damage (their arcane barrages still hit you for ~12K so having 3 of them up means you can't outheal them without IBF or AMS up). Don't ever army in P2 as this causes the Nexus Lords to scatter outside the suppression zones.\n\nPhase 3 is trivial at this item level of gear. Do a 1 1 2 3 rotation and start strafing just before a static field spawns so you don't take any damage from it, collect loot. I will note my drake was down below 100K HP a couple times even at this ilevel and if you lose your P3 stack, you're done.\n\nIt'd probably have been a bit less stressful if I dropped blood-caked blade or morbidity for rune tap and two points in WotN or blade barrier, but it only took me 3 attempts after the DS hotfix to kill.\n\nI did the fight in blood presence (the incoming P1 damage is out-healable), specced vamp blood but not rune tap,\nKill took 9:39.", "date": "2011-07-21T04:41:00-05:00", "rating": 10, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Been wanting to solo this guy on my DK for the mount.  Thanks for the info.  I would a detailed video too.", "creationdate": "2011-07-22T16:55:44-05:00", "id": 254094, "rating": -1, "commentid": 1475674, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Ishtar", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I'm glad to know its this easy to solo as a DK because I'm wanting to duo it weekly with my disc priest buddy. However I am wanting to know if Malygos 25 is duoable or not? I'm certain it won't be soloed but I'd imagine it could be 5 manned easily so duoing or trioing it is the question..", "creationdate": "2011-07-31T18:34:14-05:00", "id": 255881, "rating": -1, "commentid": 1475674, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Draintwo", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Picked up the drake the other day, finishing my need to solo this boss weekly.  At 384 item level the drake has ~340K HP and pretty much can't die as long as you don't stand in static fields. Was able to kill the boss in 8:46. You can pre-stack the hot (key 3) to 5 before the boss starts which also reduces any risk of your drake dying if your item level is in the mid-370s.  This boss is currently soloable by hunter, DK and shadow priest, and should be soloable by moonkin next patch.", "creationdate": "2011-08-28T22:25:31-05:00", "id": 261261, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1475674, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "citrique", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Add warlock and Feral druid to that. Theres a few videos about it on youtube. It's tight as feral druid, but it's doable. Got the Blue Drake today, will keep going for Azure. :)", "creationdate": "2011-10-22T22:03:03-05:00", "id": 272716, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1475674, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Fragkitty", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Good guide, I've been soloing him for a while now. Two small tips: 1) Do your best to whittle him down and stack dots when his P2 RP begins. Damage here is damage you won't have to do while on the drake. 2) When P3 begins, fly a bit outwards. This makes the balls of lightning he throws have a longer travel time before they explode, and thus makes them easier to avoid via strafing.", "creationdate": "2011-12-11T12:24:00-06:00", "id": 495740, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1475674, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "PilsnerDk", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2011-07-26T11:21:13-05:00", 3, "citrique"]}
