{"commentv2": 1, "number": 96, "id": 1487410, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "sk8r2000", "body": "Duoed by a 366 Blood DK and a 373 Boomkin Druid. It took us a few tries to get right, but it was quite easy once we figured it out; phase 1, pop all dps CDs asap; use Army on pull. Take down Malygos as normal, making sure to kill the sparks for a 50% increased damage buff. Once Phase 2 begins, enter the suppression zone and kill the 2 mobs that come down to take their discs. Work together to kill every mob, and Phase 3 will begin. Use the rotation \"1 1 2 3\"; where we went wrong a few times was straying from this rotation. [b][u]Always use \"1 1 2 3\".[/u][/b] If you dps well and stick to this rotation, you should kill the boss with a few minutes to spare; if I (DK) had better gear, we probably could have pushed dps and got the 6 minute speed kill.", "date": "2011-08-04T18:25:48-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 97, "id": 1498768, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Cracked", "body": "Soloed this today on 10 man, shadow priest with around 383 ilvl gear, will fraps it next week and post a video.\r\n\r\nHe doesn't hit extra hard in p1, and thanks to the vortex you have well enough time to heal up any hp lost. If you are lucky and get 2 sparks from the same side, that helps a lot. \r\n\r\nP2 is just mad zerg on the melee adds, remember to dispel them as they tend to rape you if they are left with the buff. Hop on the disc and multidot all 4 remaining adds. \r\n\r\nP3 is the old 1-1-2-3 rotation.", "date": "2011-08-19T17:30:34-05:00", "rating": 14, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 98, "id": 1510259, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Stefanish", "body": "How many players are needed to kill this in 25-man with average ilvl 368~370? I mean to survive P3", "date": "2011-09-04T16:27:45-05:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 99, "id": 1595796, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Espoire", "body": "Possible (and fun!) to solo as a level 85 Shadow Priest.\r\n\r\nI recommend speccing into [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=33159]2/3 Empowered Healing[/url] and [url=http://www.wowhead.com/item=42402]glyphing Inner Fire[/url] for this fight. Carrying [url=http://www.wowhead.com/item=57192]mana potions[/url] and [url=http://www.wowhead.com/item=49633]Drums of Kings[/url] may help also.\r\n\r\nStrategy below, but really, most of the fun of extreme soloing is working it out for yourself. If you're just in it for transmog gear though:[spoiler]Phase 1, full out DPS as he lands, try to get as much damage as you can before you need to heal. Save Shadowfiend or Dispersion to soak his breath attacks. If you have too much HP to proc Masochism on his melee attacks, you can let him eat a Power Spark to regain mana. Attempt to heal up during the spin cycle. Once your health drops low enough that you need to heal, de-form, and replace Mind Flay in your rotation with Flash Heal.\r\n\r\nAs you enter Phase 2, you may consider using Hymn of Hope for mana, as it will likely be tight on this phase. As soon as the Nexus Lords become attackable, unload on them. Get inside a bubble, and kill them off. While doing so, watch them for the magic buff, and mass dispel it ASAP. Once they're dead, hop on a disc and DPS the Scions down. Do [i]not[/i] fly into the air, instead, remain on the ground inside the bubbles, as this will reduce damage taken from the Scions significantly. When Malygos is about to deep breathe, then fly high enough that it will not tick on you, and return to the ground afterwards.\r\n\r\nOnce the Scions are down, heal up, mana up, and fall onto your new drake.\r\n\r\nDuring the initial monologue in Phase 3, stack up action 3 on yourself to 5 stacks. Once Malygos becomes attackable, begin the rotation: 1123. Be careful not to get close enough for him to melee you, get out of the lightning clouds, and if you cleared the previous phases fast enough, he'll go down without much difficulty.\r\n\r\nIf you're having trouble with berserk timer, and you're close to defeating him, try to fight from a high altitude in the final phase. After your drake dies, it will take longer for you to fall to your death, allowing the drake's DoT to tick a few extra times, and you to do some damage with instant casts.[/spoiler]", "date": "2011-12-13T23:29:01-06:00", "rating": 9, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 100, "id": 1617017, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "eDGe87", "body": "Soloed the 10 man version as ret in 397 gear very easilly.\n\nUsed some talents to make soloing viable, ie: 2/2 selfless healer and 2/2 last word, and a point in sacred shield ofc. Glyphed wog + glyphed DP.\n\nP1: Started with seal of insight and just kept a normal rotation. Wog heals whenever sub 35% hp to get that monster crit (esp with sacred shield up). After I had 2 sparks down on top of eachother I switched to SoV and popped all my cds + str pot. Used Devotion aura all the time, and DP on every breath I could.\n\nP2: Just killed one of the scions on the ground, hopped on his disc and killed the rest. Easy phase but there's some damage, so be sure to heal yourself up.\n\nP3: Easiest phase. Spam your heal and keep it at 5 stacks before Malygos becomes targetable.\nThen use the following rotation: 1-1-2-3. I just strafed right every time he put that electrical cloud up. You can't die if you keep the 5 healing stacks up, as they almost out heal his damage. He died with 22 stacks up from the fire debuff (button 2). My drake was at about 85% health when Malygos died, so no worries if it ever dying if you keep this rotation up.\n\nGL farming that mount.", "date": "2012-01-26T05:33:03-06:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Yea no phase 3 is impossible for me to do. I dodge every single thing and keep up 5 stacks and by the times I have 9 flame stacks on him im at 30% hp with 398 ilvl. Not sure how you managed to heal so much", "creationdate": "2012-03-24T03:51:14-05:00", "id": 530051, "rating": -1, "commentid": 1617017, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Xiberion", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-01-26T05:35:26-06:00", 2, "eDGe87"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 101, "id": 1620669, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Nobbel", "body": "A video guide on how to solo Malygos as a retribution paladin:\r\nhttp://youtu.be/aoI5MeLD_PE?hd=1\r\n\r\nHope it will help!\r\n\r\nNobbel.", "date": "2012-02-03T10:44:37-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 384, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This helped a lot. Thanks!!", "creationdate": "2012-10-13T16:50:49-05:00", "id": 584417, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1620669, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "932363", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 102, "id": 1621698, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "410866", "body": "http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NuwglLV5N6k\r\nshadow priest can do something with this boss", "date": "2012-02-05T07:32:06-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 103, "id": 1637414, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Thoke", "body": "Just managed to solo this with a warrior (390 ilvl, dps gear + prot spec) after seeing a video about it. Not too difficult to be honest, only took me about 5 tries and most of the wipes were due silly mistakes like letting spark through.\n\nHowever he enraged and killed me half a second before he died on the dot. So I released and ran in to get my loot. But when I opened the chest it contained only money and no other items. As soon as I looted the money, the chest disappeared. \n\nJust a little heads up for anyone soloing him. Try to stay alive or this might happen.\n\n[b]Update:[/b] Contacted a GM and he send me the items that dropped without any questions asked.", "date": "2012-03-09T13:05:42-06:00", "rating": 4, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-03-11T14:45:07-05:00", 2, "Thoke"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 104, "id": 1639013, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "aphistis", "body": "Straightforward solo encounter with my ilvl 396 hunter using turtle pet spec'ed for max survivability. Pushing through the first two phases is simple, with the drake phase giving me a little trouble at first because I wasn't playing WoW when Malygos was current content. I use my base 7/31/3 MM solo spec, glyphed for Arcane Shot/Steady Shot/Kill Shot, Misdirection/Mend Pet/Disengage, Feign Death/whatever/whatever. I don't use my T5 set for Malygos. His hard enrage is 10 minutes.\r\n\r\nPhase 1: \r\n- Fairly standard tank & spank. Misdirect, mend pet. etc.\r\n- Make sure you're flanking boss to avoid breath. \r\n- Spark buffs are helpful when I can get them, but I usually have several of them reach Malygos without any noticeable increase in pet healing burden.\r\n- Continue dps'ing boss during Vortex\r\n- NOTE: As others have noted, Vortex will despawn your pet leaving you vulnerable when Vortex ends. I resummon pet with 1 second of Vortex remaining, immediately disengage toward the edge to draw boss away from Yertle (pet). Letting boss take one melee swing at me, then feigning death to reset aggro, ensures enough time for pet health to rebuff.\r\n\r\nPhase 2:\r\n- Starts at 50% boss health. If you can get here within 3 minutes of starting the fight, you're in excellent shape.\r\n- Boss will drone on and on about some damned thing or other, ignore speech and continue dps'ing until he flies out of range and adds appear\r\n- Other people's comments regarding which adds are which might be helpful, but I honestly didn't pay much attention. If it had a red nameplate, it needed to die.\r\n- Boss creates purple buff zones on ground that reduce damage but shrink over time. This will create minimum range issues with ground adds. Attacking from inside a different bubble is ideal, but if necessary a reasonably geared hunter can survive outside the bubbles for long enough to kill a handful of adds at range.\r\n- Be careful not to let flying adds get behind you overhead. Keep 'em in front of you.\r\n- I've tried using discs and dps'ing from the ground. Easier and faster for me to just range adds down from the ground and soak the boss special attacks from inside a bubble. I've never had health issues doing that way, and chasing adds around on a disc is more trouble than it's worth.\r\n\r\nPhase 3:\r\n- NOTE: This phase takes at least three minutes and you can't reset the fight once it begins. If you don't win, you have to waste time wiping, running back, rebuffing, all that. If you won't make phase 3 with at least 3 minutes left to enrage, seriously consider resetting the encounter (deterrence -> dismiss pet -> feign death) to save yourself time in the long run.\r\n- Starts when phase 2 adds are all dead\r\n- Vehicle phase using drake mount\r\n- Read other people's comments for the rotation, but I pre-stack 5 hots and then do 1/1/2/3 ad infinitum same as others\r\n- You don't have to spam the abilities as fast as possible. I tried this at first and had big problems with the #2 dot stacks falling off before I could renew them. Just go a nice steady pace progressing through the rotation one button every second or two. You'll keep your hot stacks up, your dot stacks up, and your drake's energy up.\r\n- Ignore Surge of Power. Your hot stacks will heal through it.\r\n- Strafe clear of Static Field when boss casts. Your hot stacks will NOT heal through it.\r\n- Don't panic, at the start of this phase it looks like you'll never beat the enrage timer. Just keep adding your stacks and your damage will increase throughout the phase.\r\n- If you're having visibility issues, increasing your max camera distance and panning back can be helpful.\r\n\r\nCollect lootz, partake of lulz, brag to friendz.\r\n\r\nThis is my first wowhead comment, so I help it's helpful to someone!", "date": "2012-03-13T10:57:39-05:00", "rating": 126, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Still exactly how to do P3 at 90. worked great, ty!", "creationdate": "2012-10-26T23:17:08-05:00", "id": 591441, "rating": 21, "commentid": 1639013, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "kkronc", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "This worked awesome, thank you. I was spamming my buttons and kept dying... as soon as I started taking my time, I beat him the first try! And I got my pretty azure drake :D", "creationdate": "2012-12-02T00:19:12-06:00", "id": 606294, "rating": 5, "commentid": 1639013, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Dalarya", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Thanks so much for this!! Rotation still works perfectly, no drake yet, but will keep at it :) Edit: Finally got the blue drake, will keep trying for the Azure :) This comment needs to be at the top, solo tips are always to far down the page :(", "creationdate": "2013-11-10T15:43:23-06:00", "id": 707072, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1639013, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Lyrrick", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "90 Ret Pally solo easy with this rotation.. exactly as stated above.. Hit 3 five times to stack your HoT.. then 1, 1, 2, 3 pause.. 1, 1, 2, 3 pause.. etc. if you're going too fast you'll have a small pause before you can hit 2.. but just wait for it.. then continue. Oh and of course stay on the move to keep out of Static Fields. The rotation does not work if Malygos is behind you. So just keep her in front or to your side as you fly round her, and you're golden.", "creationdate": "2014-06-16T05:19:21-05:00", "id": 751612, "rating": 3, "commentid": 1639013, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "thisguyyouknow", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 105, "id": 1648754, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "wilosoft", "body": "Soloed him for the first time as Blood DK 396 ilvl with dps gear, everything was till phase 3, I messed up 2 times with 1-1-2-3 xD but at the third time I downed him with no problem ^^, no mount though :<", "date": "2012-04-04T12:08:35-05:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 106, "id": 1656465, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Zephytoth", "body": "Blood dk, 399 lev full dps gear done.\r\nTips: \r\n-try to get 2 sparks on top of each other.\r\n-on last sparks before 50% mark, try to do as much dps as possible. Icy Touch, Death Coil & such.\r\n-don't remember if melee hits hit on the whirlwind part, but you can Icy Touch, Death Coil and Blood Boil at least, as well as Outbreak.\r\n-last phase, stack button 3 up to 5 stacks, then keep it up until phase starts. STAY OUTSIDE of his melee, I stood at max range for button 1 to hit, was far enough. \r\n-just keep on 1-1-2-3 & repeat. Don't panic, just keep at it. Max range & move out of sparks with 5 stacks, you just cannot die.", "date": "2012-04-20T10:31:24-05:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 107, "id": 1660243, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "g33ky", "body": "Yo. Soloed this last night on my DK.\r\n\r\nFirst of all: DPS race like others have said.\r\nI first tried with a mix of tank and dps gear in blood spec (about 382 ilvl) and he enraged at 1.7 mill or so...\r\nFlew back in, equipped full dps gear + 2 hander (379 ilvl) and it went pretty smoth. I changed to my dps weaps (frost dual wield) to raise my ilvl to 381 for last phase as dragons scales with ilvl, altho i'm not sure how much those 3 ilvls helped hehe.\r\n\r\nI also took a few risky choises at start of phase 3 as i only did 1,2,3 rotation like 3-4 times to build up the stack quicker at first before doing 1,1,2,3. And i have to say i almost lost the stack when i got it to 3 or 4 cause of the short duration of only 1x the combo point stacker.\r\n\r\nAfter that I just had to stay out of the lightning and keep up both the HoT and the DoT for a nice kill. No idea how close i was to enrage the secon time tho, cause i have no timer addon\r\n\r\nNo mount but was really fun to solo, harder than onyxia, easier than Kael'thas imo hehe.\r\nGL to everyone else planing/trying to solo him! :)", "date": "2012-04-29T08:28:28-05:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 108, "id": 1667166, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "aphistis", "body": "My YouTube video guide for soloing Malygos 10 as a hunter, with the strategy outlined in my previous post:\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=I-_8sDA7DDU\r\n\r\nGood luck & happy hunting!", "date": "2012-05-15T11:43:59-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 109, "id": 1675434, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "triggz", "body": "I don't know how this isn't mentioned anywhere.. but if you're having issues with Malygos wrecking your dragon in Phase 3, move out 30 yards away from him. He spams [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=57432]Arcane Pulse[/url].", "date": "2012-06-11T00:57:36-05:00", "rating": 24, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
