{"commentv2": 1, "number": 112, "id": 1691782, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Zurgzurg", "body": "I'm able to successfully solo Maly now without wiping every time after I changed my strategy and thought it would be helpful for others.\r\n\r\nAs a Blood DK in dps gear, I was still struggling with the traditional 1-1-2-3 rotation. I started experimenting with different rotations that eventually led me to find one that I have yet to die on. Normally I start the fight by stacking 3-3-3-3-3 (5 times), then go into my normal rotation which consists of 1-1-1-2-3-3-3 with that rotation I have been able to kill him always before enrage and never get close to dying. Hope it helps!", "date": "2012-07-24T16:39:45-05:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Perfect, thanks. Though i didnt use more then 1 '3' once the rotation started since it just refresh's the hot already on you :)", "creationdate": "2012-10-09T17:44:27-05:00", "id": 582128, "rating": -1, "commentid": 1691782, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "MetalGenocide", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "It's a spam rotation. Designed to keep your fingers active when there's nothing more benefitial to do. The idea is to keep as much HOT up on yourself as possible without risking losing either it or the DOT. Get your HOT up to five stacks then bounce three '1's followed by one '2', then, three '3's. The reason for three '3's is the cd on '2' can take a while and going back to '1' straight away can risk you losing either HOT, DOT or both. This method is foolproof. Thanks, Zurgzurg.", "creationdate": "2012-10-13T11:26:42-05:00", "id": 584233, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1691782, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Eekwibble", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 113, "id": 1705948, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "410866", "body": "Shadow priest solo Malygos 25\r\nhttp://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KprjL7OswGQ", "date": "2012-08-29T21:07:37-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 114, "id": 1735338, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "duranox", "body": "My tactic for the Mounted phase was the following, start by getting 5 stacks on the HOT on you then use the healing ability, after that start attacking and when you see the HOT is about to run out refresh it, but the most important thing is to keep the debuff up on Malygos all the time. If it falls then it's a big chance you'll not beat the enrage timer", "date": "2012-10-08T06:56:03-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 115, "id": 1737130, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Hashupa", "body": "This was extremely easy as a BM hunter. I fought him in heroic dungeon gear, which probably doesn't even matter. I even used a spirit beast for the quick self heal, but I did not need it at all.\r\n\r\nAs a hunter, just keep your pet set to tenacity. Once you start riding the drake, cycle 1-1-2-3 over and over while flying in circles around him. My drake never dropped below 90% health this way and I was able to take him down in less than 5 minutes.\r\n\r\nFarm this quick for the Blue and Azure drakes before they go the way of the old ZG mounts!", "date": "2012-10-10T02:40:14-05:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Survival with a ferocity pet works just as well. [url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vp5mhoACagU]Video[/url]", "creationdate": "2012-10-26T12:49:34-05:00", "id": 591244, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1737130, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Cinnamohn", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Your strategy worked like a charm, was really easy. Killed him as a SV hunter in heroic gear although I dont think gear matters too much at this point. As Hashupa said - fly around and avoid stuff Maly throws at you pressing 1,1,2 to keep the stacks up on boss and then 3 to keep healing stacks on you. My drake never fell below 80% HP.", "creationdate": "2012-11-09T02:01:53-06:00", "id": 597014, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1737130, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "bobrock1982", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 116, "id": 1755335, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "1051634", "body": "Just solo'd him as Feral Druid on 25-Mode:\r\n\r\nMaly enraged in P2, i stopped before killing the last add, waited 30 minutes for deenrage, then killed him in P3 with much time.\r\nDon't know, if he will enrage again, but you've plenty of time when doing it like this.\r\n\r\nWhole fight took like 55 mins.\r\nNo mount ... -.-", "date": "2012-11-02T03:10:34-05:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 16384, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "The Scions of Eternity (and I presume Nexus Lords) actually Berserk along with him! Good thing it doesn't appear to do anything (their 18k Arcane Barrages stayed 18k), so all it relly does is make it easier to keep track of the timer as Malygos isn't targetable in phase 2. I had to wait so long for the Berserk (a good 5 minutes) that I'm starting to wonder if I could have just pushed to phase 3 and killed him with the drake... Next week, I guess.", "creationdate": "2012-12-11T23:05:57-06:00", "id": 610756, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1755335, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Arbron", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 117, "id": 1758251, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "1053035", "body": "I have done this with a partner at lvl 90, and we were fine. Simply know what to use in the last phase. (hit 1st ability five times and DOT ability, heal 5 times, and keep up heal between applying dots.) It should be like: 1 1 1 1 1 2, 3 3 3 3 3, 1 1 1 1 2, 3, 1 1 1 1 1 2. I've seen this solo'd as well, by stacking up to 25 long-term DOT's (2) on Malygos. This will be the tough part solo'ing at lvl 90.\r\n\r\nAlso, we tried to two man the 25-man and we're not sure if this is possible. The 10 man drops both drakes, so I don't know why you would bother other than for the achievement. In that case, you will need several more people, I'm guessing at least 4 who know how to use the drakes.", "date": "2012-11-06T13:29:51-06:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 16384, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 118, "id": 1759388, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Gulanga", "body": "Today I able to solo a [url=http://www.wowhead.com/achievement=1874]Speed Kill[/url] of him in 10man mode as a dps warrior.\r\nNo mount drop though (and yes both mounts do drop in 10man mode).\r\n\r\nIt was not very hard, just save all cd's till about 60-65% so you can get him low enough before P2 to not spend much time in P3. A spark helps.\r\nIn P3 just use x3 \"[url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=56091]1[/url]\" followed by a \"[url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=56092]2[/url]\" until you get down to 50% life then weave in some [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=57090]healing[/url] in between. The reason you want 3x charge is that the dot lasts longer that way so you have time for healing as well as next dot. Don't let the dot fall off.\r\nThe other abilities are not needed. \r\nAs ranged this should be even easier.", "date": "2012-11-08T16:12:25-06:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 119, "id": 1763173, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Seahnjin", "body": "As of MoP, the 10-man version can be soloed by pretty much anyone. Honestly, if I was able to do it on my first try as a badly geared 90 rogue (after reading the strat for phase 3, of course... because I never really did that one daily and I suck at it so much), then so can you.\nOf course, the more DPS you can put out on the first two phases, the more room you have for mistakes in phase 3, in case you're just as uncoordinated as I am. Killing the sparks in phase 1 and grabbing the buff for yourself definitely helps.\n\n10-man is also all you're going to need unless you want the 25-man achievements, as the Azure Drake and the cool weapon transmogs all drop from this version.", "date": "2012-11-16T04:35:55-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-12-06T05:57:33-06:00", 2, "Seahnjin"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 120, "id": 1764042, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Silvansaria", "body": "I absolutely cannot solo this encounter - I don't know what I'm doing wrong....\n\nI can get through Phase 1 and 2 no problem and bring him to about half life or less going into Phase 3.  I jump on the drake - and spam up #2 five times while he is sitting there talking and then seems no matter what rotation I try or what I do - his health NEVER moves past like 25% no matter what...\n\nI've tried the 1,1,1,1,1,2,3,3,3,1,1 and the 1,1,12,3,3,3 and the 1,1,2,3 like some of the video on YouTube suggest - and it doesn't matter.  I keep strafing to the left or right avoiding those lightning blasts he throws out...  No matter what I seem to do - his health never moves past 25%, he enrages and even if I have full life and my drake has full energy - we die.\n\n...wtf is wrong here?\n\nMaybe I'm not understanding the combo points you have to stack correctly or I'm not understanding exactly how the rotation works but I have copied exactly what I've seen and read and nothing - fail every damn time.\n\nAny ideas what I'm doing wrong or maybe NOT doing?", "date": "2012-11-18T00:19:42-06:00", "rating": -6, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "1, 1, 2, 3 is the way to go. Strictly stick to this strategy and never go out of your way to break it. Ignore the other abilities altogether. The key is to stack the 2 DoT. If you don't have enough energy to cast 2, just wait until you do and then continue.", "creationdate": "2012-11-18T11:16:13-06:00", "id": 600387, "rating": 8, "commentid": 1764042, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Bobrik", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I just ran into the same issue in here today. No combo points are stacking up for my friend and I so we can't really dps him at all in the last phase.", "creationdate": "2012-12-02T16:41:30-06:00", "id": 606642, "rating": -1, "commentid": 1764042, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "thranlynn", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-11-18T00:21:10-06:00", 1, "Silvansaria"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 121, "id": 1767489, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Chaosrock", "body": "He dropped both the Azure and the Blue drake for me tonight.", "date": "2012-11-25T03:47:23-06:00", "rating": -10, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 122, "id": 1769504, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Solacia", "body": "really easy to solo as a ranged class at 90, at least on 10 man\r\n\r\nGet two sparks stacked and force transition to phase 2, then pop all cooldowns and burst as hard as you can before he flies out of range. I hit phase 3 with 1 HP left, which meant I just had to hit the 1 button only once when he came up in phase 3 for a win. No dodgy drake/vehicle mechanics to worry about.", "date": "2012-11-28T02:29:00-06:00", "rating": 24, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 123, "id": 1787532, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "superdx", "body": "I just did this as a 482 Fury Warrior. Always manage to nuke him down to about 20-30% but still need to do the last phase on the drakes. I assume this would be true for most melee classes.\n\nInstead of using those preset sequences, here's what I did. You only need abilities 1, 2 and 3 and a mod that can watch combo points + the dot debuff. \n\n1. Get 5 stacks on the boss by pressing 1\n2. Use 2\n3. Slam 3 to heal yourself in between  (avoid the sparks AOE, you can't do anything about that stare though)\n4. 10-15s left on the dot, repeat 1 (do it at 20s left if you can)\n\nDid this cycle maybe 3-4 times and it was dead. P3 lasts about 1-2 mins.\n\n(optional) if you find yourself with only < 5s left, don't let the dot fall off, refresh it by 1 and then immediately 2. Buy yourself some time to get another 5-stack dot up. But it shouldn't be necessary unless you are about to die. \n\nThe dot on the boss is what kills it. So you need to keep it up. I killed it with about 5-6 stacks on the boss.", "date": "2012-12-26T02:54:08-06:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2012-12-26T03:23:14-06:00", 2, "superdx"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 124, "id": 1788390, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Chakra", "body": "[b][u]Solo Malygos (Drake Phase):[/u][/b]\n\nStart with hotting yourself to 5 stacks then do the following:\n\n[b]1)[/b] 5x DoT Malygos + Engulf In Flames.\n[b]2)[/b] Immediatly HoT yourself to refresh it.\n[b]3)[/b] Wait for full energy, then HoT yourself again.\n[b]4)[/b] Repeat from step 1.", "date": "2012-12-27T22:30:30-06:00", "rating": -7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2013-01-17T23:56:58-06:00", 1, "Chakra"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 125, "id": 1789313, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "91976", "body": "You can't actually kill him until phase 3 starts. He'll be stuck at 1 hp if you do enough damage during phase 1/2.", "date": "2012-12-29T21:29:55-06:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Phase 3 would be really easy then. Unless he gets bugged out at 1HP in Phase 2?", "creationdate": "2013-01-10T20:20:13-06:00", "id": 621337, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1789313, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "superdx", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I got him to 1HP in phase 1 today on my Elemental Shaman, he does just stay at that no matter how many extra spells hit him or if DOTs are on him, once phase 3 started the first attack killed him.", "creationdate": "2013-04-05T07:18:19-05:00", "id": 648554, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1789313, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "1105496", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 126, "id": 1805780, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "dragancla", "body": "Patch 5.1, I can confirm that both Azure Drake and Blue Drake have a chance to drop on 10-man. Proof below: \n\nhttp://i169.photobucket.com/albums/u210/dragancla/WoW/wtf_zpsdb4caaf3.jpg", "date": "2013-01-28T17:50:28-06:00", "rating": 12, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2014-10-12T21:24:01-05:00", 1, "dragancla"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 127, "id": 1807437, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "SlapMyNipples", "body": "Killed him now Solo as Blood DK lvl 90 ilvl 480.\r\n\r\nPhase 1 isnt hard at all, just nuke him with.\r\n\r\nPhase 2 can be tricky for classes with no heal spells, but for blood DK it's not aproblem, just kill the 2 mobs on the platform, hop on a disc and killed the remaining 4 mobs.\r\n\r\nPhase 3 can be tricky if you don't now what to do. What you have to do is press: 1, 1, 2, 3. DONT SPAM. If you spam you're not going to make it! Find a nice pace. I find out that after I press 3, I should watch my healing stack until it has 6 seconds left (from 10 seconds) and when I did that, my #2 was usable again. Just keep this pace and you will kill him in a few minutes.\r\n\r\nGood luck! :)", "date": "2013-01-31T21:48:33-06:00", "rating": 1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 128, "id": 1811329, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "329396", "body": "Just solo'd the 25m version on my warlock.  My gear is 491 ilvl.  I'm affliction specced, using a voidwalker with grimoire of supremacy and soul link.\r\n\r\nThere's a bit of a bug with the boss, or it's not mentioned in the fight description.  There's an aggro reset after the vortex.  And as a warlock, it took a good while before my pet picked up aggro again (like 30 sec or so).  So you have a couple of options, either tank him yourself after the vortex, with the voidwalker whacking on him for about 30 sec till he re-establishes aggro, or you can soulshatter.  Soulshatter will return the aggro to your voidwalker, but it's on a 2 minute cooldown, so if you hit another vortex, you're going to face the exact same problem.  You will probably only face 2 vortexes, so your best bet is to shatter the first one, then just tank the 2nd one while using the proper defensive cooldowns and a healthstone.\r\n\r\nThis takes you into p2, because getting him to 50% was not difficult.  In p2, make sure you get your voids on the 4 melee guys, and dot them up.  It helps to kill the melee guys as quick as possible, because with all 4 of  them whacking on you, it can tax your health more than you would expect.  But if you just focus them down, it will be easy going until p3.  I use the glyph of corruption that gives you back some health whenever it ticks....so i would just dot up as many of the scions as possible and you'll get plenty of self healing from it.  the scions have less than 400k health, so you can easily focus them down one at a time or just dot them all as they circle around you in the air.  \r\n\r\nonce you get to p3, its just like everyone else in the thread says...quickly get yourself to 5 stacks of the hot (number 3), then once maly becomes targetable, just concentrate on doing 1-1-2-3, then repeat that sequence until he dies.  1-1-2-3 will do two things...it will keep your stack of hots on yourself, and it will slowly build a stack of dmg to maly.  On 25 man, it took a while for him to go down.  His health will not change much until you start getting your dps stacks around 20, then you will notice his percentage will start dropping.  If you find you make a mistake with your rotation and have to choose between dropping your hots or dropping your dps stack, keep the dps stack up or you probably won't survive.  It's much easier to regain your 5 stack of hots than a 20 stack of dmg.  \r\n\r\nI hate to be \"that guy\" but the mount dropped the first time, so I can't really tell you if blizz changed it to 100% chance now, or if I just got lucky.  Good luck.", "date": "2013-02-09T12:53:38-06:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "I just \"accidentally\" solo'd Maly on 25 man after forgetting to change to 10. Demo lock 474 item level, he enraged just as my last \"number 3\" skill (can't remember the name) hit, heh. Mount didn't drop. Oh, and it's not a bug after the vortex phase, your pet despawns and a new one pops when you land. ;)", "creationdate": "2013-02-13T08:42:20-06:00", "id": 632317, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1811329, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "LyssaWoW", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 129, "id": 1813513, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "kingja", "body": "Solo'ed as SV Hunter, gear is 483ilvl. When ever I solo old raid content I always think about going BM and using a spirit beast for the heal it has but in this fight I did not need it. Use MD at the beginning and nuke down the boss, when P2 begins MD again so the 2 Nexus Lords aggro your pet, bring them down then hop on to the hover disc and kill the remaining 4 mobs flying around.\r\n\r\nDoing that will start P3 and easily the most challenging part of the fight [b]IF[u][/u][/b] you dont the rotation for your new moves that you have on your dragon. I myself died a few times, needlessly spamming all the buttons or not getting the balance right between dps and healing. As soon as you gain control of your dragon use \"3\" and stack it up 5 times, 3 is your HoT that will keep you alive. By the time it reaches 5 Malygos should become active, all you need to do is follow the set pattern as many users have said in the comments of \"1-1-2-3\". Your damage may not seem that good and Maly's hp might not look like its going down at first but following this pattern you will hardly lose any health and his health will go down alot quicker as the fight progresses and the DoT from \"2\" starts stacking up. Also move out of and avoid the lightning AoE that he casts for needless damage.\r\n\r\nBar that just be patient, if you have hit 1 twice but 2 is not useable yet just wait till it is and then 3 and rinse and repeat. At 90 I think any class could do this without any problems its just learning P3 and getting used to it.\r\n\r\nI also hate to be that guy but my first time doing Malygos, he dropped the Azure Drake. If only all the other mounts and transmorg items I want would be as kind :D", "date": "2013-02-14T10:11:21-06:00", "rating": -2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 130, "id": 1815081, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "heqno", "body": "For some weird reason i cant get him down in P3 , doing like everyone said here on comments with the 1,1,2,3 , also tried 5 a couple of times, Frost DK 364 ilvl ..", "date": "2013-02-18T06:11:41-06:00", "rating": -6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "probably not moving enough out of bad stuff, i do it on 89 hunter with little problems, best of luck :) 1123, but dont' rush it, keep your energy high an stacks on", "creationdate": "2013-02-19T00:23:09-06:00", "id": 633934, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1815081, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Drummel", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 131, "id": 1823036, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Syloswift", "body": "Attempted to solo - Patch 5.2 - Level 90 Paladin\r\n\r\nFirst two phases are simple, I popped all my CD's and nuked him, occasionally casting a heal. The real problem is the last phase. It is easy enough to keep your dragon alive and DPS at the same time, but as it is effectively doing a level 80's damage against Malygos, you hit the enrage timer.\r\n\r\nI got him down to 1M HP before the enrage so I would imagine that it is very possible to two-man it.", "date": "2013-03-06T18:21:25-06:00", "rating": -7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Your damage in P3 scales with your iLvl. Wear your highest iLvl gear, and follow 1, 1, 2, 3, repeat. Don't freak out when you don't have enough energy to hit #2, just wait and press it, then quickly hit #3. Changing the rotation let's the stacks on her fall off. With lots of stacks, you'll be doing 200k+ hits (not so much level 80 damage anymore ;-)", "creationdate": "2013-03-09T05:01:53-06:00", "id": 639488, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1823036, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "smackthekids", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 132, "id": 1825088, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "smackthekids", "body": "Just solo'd 25 man w/ ilvl 485 Fury Warrior. Even with awesome DPS, u really need to practice P3 to get the rotation down. Even 1 screw up and you'll hit enrage if your stacks fall off. Ranged don't have as big of a problem as they can take down a big chunk of her HP during the phase transition, eliminating a lot of P3's up time. No mount, but REALLY glad to know its possible without cheating like they do on all the YouTube videos I've seen (let boss enrage before the final P3 push, sit in pink bubble for 30min until enrage wears off, then continue to take minutes, hours, days, however long u want to finish her in P3 without her ever re-enraging.)\r\nGood luck to everyone on farming her mount!", "date": "2013-03-09T04:58:47-06:00", "rating": -5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 133, "id": 1828035, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Nakae", "body": "Ridiculously easy to solo as an ilvl 477 survival hunter with any pet.\r\n\r\nPhase 1 - Stand behind Malygos, to avoid his bad breath.  One-shot the sparks when they get on the platform, and stand in their gooey electrified corpses.  Keep firing at him during the vortex - the only issue here is that your pet despawns, so all aggro goes to you.  Feign death once he lands again to keep him chomping on your pet and not you.\r\n\r\nPhase 2 - not difficult.  Keep moving around - the balls of purple-blue fire are targeted at the ground, not you.  Shoot down the floating magic-men that come towards you, and steal their floating discs to get to the smart, higher-up magic-men.\r\n\r\nPhase 3 - ... lol?  Stack up the HoT, then 1, 1, 2, 3 once he's targetable.  You're invincible, he's on fire, and then he falls to oblivion.  All is good.  Collect loot.\r\n\r\nI don't even bother with mend pet - I have a tenacity turtle, but he never loses more than 10k healther before [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=109212]Spirit Bond[/url] heals him up again, and he's never proc'ed [url=http://www.wowhead.com/spell=26064]Shell Shield[/url] before on this fight.\r\n\r\nHe dropped Azure Drake my first run, but not a scale nor horn of Blue Drake yet.", "date": "2013-03-13T12:50:00-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 134, "id": 1830572, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Dracoandy", "body": "Just did this raid on 10 man and can confirm that the Blue Drake does still drop from Malygos,", "date": "2013-03-18T07:55:34-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 135, "id": 1837481, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "968833", "body": "Just press 1, 1 , 2, 3 and keep doing circles around him\r\n\r\nWhen he has about 20 stacks on him his health just disintegrates and dies", "date": "2013-04-01T06:26:59-05:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 136, "id": 1838991, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Sluggzo", "body": "If you're having trouble getting through phase 3 solo with the 1-1-2-3 rotation, I found it easiest to let your energy fully recharge between 2 and 3. This build a solid rhythm where my stacks never dropped and my health regenned enough to stay ahead of his damage.", "date": "2013-04-04T13:26:04-05:00", "rating": -1, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 137, "id": 1843450, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "1114907", "body": "Before phase 3 starts, build up your health buff to 5 stacks by pressing button 3, once the fight starts it will give you a head start, then stick to button rotation 1,1,2,3.\r\n\r\nvoila", "date": "2013-04-15T12:29:11-05:00", "rating": 35, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "this makes it trivial. cheers.", "creationdate": "2013-04-27T03:03:33-05:00", "id": 654124, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1843450, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "kerrymayall", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Using the combination of many methods above, most of which are 1 1 2 3, but then finally finding and using this one, piece of cake. He died, I was at 100% health. Thanks bud!", "creationdate": "2013-06-07T07:57:59-05:00", "id": 666850, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1843450, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "TriesteHunter", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Awesome thank u :) this worked perfectly, was a doddle, and the blue drake dropped on my first try.", "creationdate": "2013-09-24T05:57:29-05:00", "id": 695965, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1843450, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Lottielot", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
