{"commentv2": 1, "number": 148, "id": 1866536, "nreplies": 11, "sticky": 0, "user": "Narinae", "body": "The Beginner's Guide to Soloing Malygos:\n\n[i]Edit: As of 6.0, soloing instances that you've outlevelled is a LOT easier. I'll leave this writeup intact for those who want to try at lower levels, but anyone level 90+ will have Malygos nearly dead when phase 3 starts.[/i]\n\nSet your raid difficulty. The mounts are just as likely to drop in 10-man as in 25, so I'll assume that's what you're doing. At lvl 90 you shouldn't have much trouble with 10-man. Enter the instance by taking the top-most portal inside the spire at The Nexus in Coldarra, Borean Tundra.\n\nStart the fight by clicking the big orb in the middle of the platform. Beat Malygos down. Sparks will spawn; you can kill or ignore them. When Malygos becomes untargetable, phase 2 has started. \n\nAdds will spawn on hoverboards. Kill one and get on their hoverboard. Fly around killing the other adds. Stay well above the main platform, so you don't get hit by what Malygos is throwing out. When the last hoverboard add is killed, phase 3 starts.\n\nYou are plopped on the back of a red drake. You have three buttons of interest here:\n1 - direct damage\n2 - stacking damage over time\n3 - self heal over time\n\nStart pressing 3 immediately upon landing on your red drake. You should be able to get a full stack of five going before Malygos engages. Fly up a little so you can see him. Target him when he becomes targetable and start your casting rotation: 1, 1, 2, 3. At times you will have to wait for the next button in your rotation to become available (usually 2). Do not skip a button! Just wait patiently until you can continue in order. \n\nHover in place, working your rotation. When Malygos hits you with the extra bright, electric-sounding cloud, strafe sideways out of it. Do not let this interrupt your rotation, even if it takes you a few extra seconds to get moved. \n\nKeep working your rotation and scooting out of the electric clouds as needed. As the stacks of your damage over time accumulate on Malygos, his health will drop more quickly.\n\nOptional: Once you can do so without interrupting your rotation, back away until you're close to max range from Malygos. He has one spell that he'll only use if you're close, so staying back will reduce the damage you take. Just don't get out of range and lose those stacks of debuff! This isn't critical in 10-man but is something to try if you're struggling, or if you want to try 25-man.\n\nOnce the fight is over, Alexstrasza appears and creates a red diamond chest next to Malygos's blue heart. Open the chest, sigh in disappointment that it doesn't contain any mounts, and click the nearby portal to exit the instance. Try again next week!", "date": "2013-06-14T09:12:29-05:00", "rating": 123, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "This is rotation works perfectly, was struggling with a low geared alt and following the above got the kill.", "creationdate": "2013-06-16T17:06:28-05:00", "id": 669631, "rating": 5, "commentid": 1866536, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "webbma", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Another very important thing to keep in mind: if you're chugging along, 1-1-2-3-ing nice and steady, then lose the stacks because you took an extra second moving or whatever, [b]DO NOT PANIC![/b] Just start the rotation over, and as long as you didn't take too long reaching phase 3 and you get the stacks going again, you should be just fine.", "creationdate": "2013-06-17T15:10:11-05:00", "id": 669909, "rating": 5, "commentid": 1866536, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "drewbster", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "It bears stating that if you *do* lose stacks, to recover, it might help to heal yourself up for a bit. Malygos is *not* going to enrage if you're level 90, he *will* die first, so taking the time to top yourself off [select yourself and 3-3-3-4, more or less 3s depending on how low you are] won't hurt your chances to succeed. Also a good idea to do if for some reason you haven't lost your stacks but you're about to die somehow. Better to lose stacks than to wipe and have to start over.", "creationdate": "2013-07-16T19:18:55-05:00", "id": 678009, "rating": 4, "commentid": 1866536, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "LostDrewid", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Well, at 90, Malygos 10 has about 6 mio life. That means that with any dot class, he is practically dead when you mount on that drake... ^^", "creationdate": "2013-10-08T17:36:09-05:00", "id": 699771, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1866536, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Qtena", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Thank ya muchly. This did the trick! No mounts this run, but the kill went smoothly once I got into a nice rhythm of button presses and strafing. :D", "creationdate": "2013-10-10T10:50:23-05:00", "id": 700167, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1866536, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Shashos", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2014-12-04T12:15:24-06:00", 6, "Narinae"]}
