{"commentv2": 1, "number": 157, "id": 1924435, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Mmaster", "body": "[i]For ranged characters trying to solo Malygos, here is a great addition to the strategies posted below.[/i]\r\n\r\nWhen Malygos transitions from Phase One to Phase Two, he does a speech and a very slow flying animation before becoming untargetable until Phase Three. This was usually when most cooldowns were popped. However with good DPS control and Deadly Boss Mods, you can maximize this uptime to deal as much DPS as possible. Here is how to do it:\r\n\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]Start Phase One normally, but try to do as much DPS as possible, bringing him to close as 50% as possible [u]without going under[/u].[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]Wait for Vortex to sweep you in the air. Once this happens, continue DPSing, now as hard as you can without popping the big cooldowns.[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]Once Vortex is over, Malygos still needs to do a slow landing animation before doing a slow lifting animation to start his transition. Once you're on the floor, pop all cooldowns and go ham.[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\n[ul]\r\n[li]If done correctly, you will have loads of time to put a lot of hurt into him. With enough DPS, you can easily bring him down to 1% Health before Phase Two starts, making Phase Three a breeze.[/li]\r\n[/ul]\r\n\r\nHopefully this information helps people who were struggling with this encounter.", "date": "2013-12-08T10:24:23-06:00", "rating": 26, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "After about 2 hours trying to solo this with no luck I finally visited wowhead, i followed this and the 1,1,2,3 rotation and beat it first try and got all 25 man achievments. *cue the eyeroll* I feel so silly now, thnks for the info.", "creationdate": "2014-05-03T22:53:44-05:00", "id": 744019, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1924435, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Stephani3", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 158, "id": 1924757, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Kontwos", "body": "Just solo'd this on my fresh 90 Druid about 450ilvl; bleeds barely dented him past half after the fly phase. Was a bit worried about the last phase about taking too much dmg and my dmg out put on the dragon; then realized Ysera's Gift talent works on the dragon so I was constantly healing for 100k. If you do have a 85+ Druid, spec Ysera's Gift and just dps away with no worries. You'll out heal all of Maly's dps.", "date": "2013-12-09T15:09:46-06:00", "rating": 9, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 159, "id": 1936665, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Vegesmite", "body": "My wife and I on our hunters (547 & 539 ilvl) got a kill first time on 25 man, phase 1 burned to below 20% and then the trusty 1,1,2,3 rotation on phase 3 worked a treat.", "date": "2014-01-22T05:41:37-06:00", "rating": 8, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Thanks, i use your 1,1,2,3 rotation (sometimes 1,1,1,2,3) and it works like a charm! Just make sure to move out of the lightning AOE.", "creationdate": "2014-01-22T11:32:21-06:00", "id": 723469, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1936665, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Aurecante", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I'm his wife, I sometimes use 1,1,1,2,3 as well -- just don't tell Vege ;)", "creationdate": "2014-02-07T20:02:28-06:00", "id": 727149, "rating": 7, "commentid": 1936665, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "sugarbaby", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 160, "id": 1957780, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Achooah", "body": "recently Malygos has been buggy, as his loot crystal won't yield any loot, so don't try until it's fixed, and this bug is in effect as of April 11th 2014.\n\n(edit) it has been fixed, it was a minor server bug.", "date": "2014-04-11T20:07:34-05:00", "rating": 0, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Confirmed as well. Girlfriend and I attempted to do our weekly mount runs and came across the same bugged out loot. After she spoke with a GM they told her we killed the boss too fast and it didn't have time to generate a loot table. They also mentioned they haven't been updating a lot of older contents to be killed faster than before so this can happen to most of the older content. Be careful hunting", "creationdate": "2014-04-11T21:53:14-05:00", "id": 740028, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1957780, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "snypen007", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Seems fixed, wasn't bugged for me.", "creationdate": "2014-04-26T01:07:40-05:00", "id": 742570, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1957780, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "RagnorZ", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2014-05-06T20:57:08-05:00", 1, "Achooah"]}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 161, "id": 1961177, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Celebriian", "body": "I wish I had a victory success story to share here too, but I give up (for now) trying to solo Malygos, no matter how much of a loser I may seem.  I'm on a Prot Pally iLvl 515, off-spec Ret.  I tried both specs, and I get him down to half health on each, but it's the rotation on the dragon that does me in every single time.  \r\n\r\nI have been trying since Cata, following all the advice here.  I'm using the 1-1-2-3 as advised and I'm still obliterated.  I even tried 1-1-1-2-3 like one of the users here said she did at times, and I've tried with both having no stacks of heals and [i]with[/i] stacking heals up to 5x's.  Nada.  Fine.  So be it.  Maybe it works better at a higher gear level, or maybe the RNG and Rotation Gods just don't like me (since it took me 5 years to loot the Rivendare's Deathcharger from Stratholme side entrance).  I've had trouble in the Occulus as well.  Not going to waste of my gold on any more repairs or tactics that won't work for me solo in this gear level.  \r\n~yes I'm mad~", "date": "2014-04-25T20:21:45-05:00", "rating": 3, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "1-1-2-3 works but you must move out of range of the lightning balls (called static field) that do aoe damage. Start at the same height/level as the boss at south on the map, then move to west after the first ball, then move to north after the next ball, then east after the next ball. If south hasn't cleared yet move to directly below the boss, then directly above the boss. This gives you 6 locations to go too which is enough time for south to be clear again. Maximum zoomed out camera distance helps.", "creationdate": "2014-04-26T01:06:51-05:00", "id": 742569, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1961177, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "RagnorZ", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Keep rotating (flight phase) above him. When 1st field drops (which won't hit you, because you're strafing) continue rotating BELOW. When 2nd field drops, BOOM! You're golden. You don't even have to change altitude. There's plenty of space on a plane w/ him that you & 2 static fields can share it w/out taking damage. After the 2nd field, each 3rd will appear just after the 1st despawns, so watch those fields. When one despawns, he's casting the next: move toward the despawned one. You'll have all the time in the world to do any rotation you like.", "creationdate": "2014-10-01T01:17:45-05:00", "id": 775984, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1961177, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Thrope", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 162, "id": 1969958, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "Laran", "body": "[b]Strategy as a level 90 Hunter (or any ranged)\r\n[/b]\r\n[b]Phase one\r\n[/b]- Blow every single CD and bring Malygos to 1 health (can't die in 1st phase)\r\n\r\n[b]Phase two\r\n[/b]- Look awesome and kill adds\r\n\r\n[i](insert nap time due to RP)[/i]\r\n\r\n[b]Phase three\r\n[/b]- Hit Malygos once\r\n\r\nProfit!\r\n\r\n- The End", "date": "2014-06-04T00:49:32-05:00", "rating": 7, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "this is spot on. worked like a charm as a 564 hunter", "creationdate": "2014-07-11T23:34:29-05:00", "id": 756845, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1969958, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "borcar", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Lol yeah i do that every time on my 533 hunter, its super easy", "creationdate": "2014-07-18T21:43:54-05:00", "id": 758440, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1969958, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "huntersvenka", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
