{"commentv2": 1, "number": 165, "id": 1991989, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Zeridian", "body": "As of 5.4 and before\r\n\r\nthis is easily soloable by 90s.\r\n\r\nJust beat him down like normal until he flies.\r\n\r\nKill nexus lords, jump on hover discs, Kill scions.\r\n\r\nInitiate phase 3:\r\n1) Begin by stacking up your 3 skill 5X\r\n2) Press order 1,1,2,3 (if you're mashing 1, and overmash you will not be able to keep your 3 stacks up.\r\n3) Dodge sparks, or move out of them\r\n4) you should be able to maintain your dot (2) on maly, while upkeeping your (3) and healing yourself. If your 2 is falling off, you're using too much energy. There will be a gap between 1,1, and 2.", "date": "2014-08-15T13:04:46-05:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 166, "id": 1992001, "nreplies": 1, "sticky": 0, "user": "Porrim", "body": "Just for anyone interested in soloing it: I cannot stress enough that you don't try to rush p3 (assuming you don't basically kill him beforehand) -- I was having a lot of trouble because I'd honestly forgotten that energy was a thing in p3 (in my defense, my UI was rather obtuse about it and I hadn't done the encounter since it was relevant). [b]Pace yourself.[/b]\r\n\r\nJust start off with 3 3 3 3 3, then repeat 1 1 2 3 and win. If you're getting low (I did sometimes, but I'm at 85), keep up 2 and use 1 1 4 until you get back up to a reasonable point. Not much else to say.", "date": "2014-08-15T13:35:10-05:00", "rating": 5, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Thank you! Your method worked. Started with 3-3-3-3-3 (healing boost) before the fight starts. Then just keep on hitting 1-1-2-3 (just wait patiently for 2 to be available and do not hit different sequence) while avoiding the purple bursting light floating around you. If your both side are blocked by the purple bursting light then go up higher to avoid them. [b]Watch the enemy profile for the fire icon[/b]. The number will increase as you hit 2 key. Once it reaches 10 or higher his health meter will go down faster. Just keep an eye on the numbers to go up and he will eventually die in the end.", "creationdate": "2014-09-04T03:49:54-05:00", "id": 769653, "rating": 2, "commentid": 1992001, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "midobu", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
