{"commentv2": 1, "number": 175, "id": 2073965, "nreplies": 3, "sticky": 0, "user": "brownpaw", "body": "[b]Location of the Instance[/b]\nThe instance, [url=http://www.wowhead.com/zone=4500/the-eye-of-eternity]The Eye of Eternity[/url], is located through the top-most portal inside The Nexus building in Coldarra, [url=http://www.wowhead.com/zone=3537]Borean Tundra[/url], Northrend, located northwest of Warsong Hold (Horde).  The nearest neutral flight path is called [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=27046]The Transitus Shield[/url], which should now be an auto-learned flightpath.\n\n[b]Why is this instance worth completing?[/b]\nSeveral achievements (see below for list), and two mounts: [item=43952] and [item=43953], both of which have a small chance to drop in both the 10-man/25-man difficulties (to select difficulty, right click on your portrait, go to raids, and select the difficulty that you'd like).\n\n[b]Soloing at 100, and it's your first time here?[/b]\nMalygos is [i]easily[/i] soloable at level 100.  It's also a very quick clear, as there is no trash or winding corridors -- you are able to summon the boss within seconds of entering the instance.\n\nEnter the instance and, when ready, click the orb to start the encounter.\n\n[ul]\n[li][b]Phase 1[/b], just burn him down.  Even as a caster wearing cloth, he should barely touch you at max level.[/li]\n[li][b]Phase 2[/b] consists of several [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=30249]Scion of Eternity[/url] mobs spawning, flying around on hover disks.  When one is killed, they will drop a disk which you can then ride (fly) on to more easily kill the others (see related achievement below).  Kill them all, and you will auto-dismount from the hover disk (be careful of falling damage -- don't go too high!).[/li]\n[li][b]Phase 3[/b], Malygos will destroy the floor, and you'll be caught by a drake.  With you at level 100, Malygos should already be near 1hp at this point, and a single attack or two from your drake -- mount/vehicle option 1 -- should finish him off.  Loot what spawns after he drops away, and exit the instance out of the portal that appears (it's there, just hard to see sometimes.  Don't dismount the drake as this will kill you).[/li][/ul]\n\n[b]Related Achievements[/b]\nYou should be able to get these in one go at each difficulty.  Do note that both the 10 and 25-man versions share a lockout period, so you can unfortunately only do one of them once per week per character.\n\n[ul]\n[li][b]The Spellweaver's Downfall[/b] ([url=http://www.wowhead.com/achievement=622/the-spellweavers-downfall-10-player]10man[/url] / [url=http://www.wowhead.com/achievement=623]25man[/url]) - Kill Malygos.[/li]\n\n[li][b]You Don't Have an Eternity[/b] ([url=http://www.wowhead.com/achievement=1874/you-dont-have-an-eternity-10-player]10man[/url] / [url=http://www.wowhead.com/achievement=1875/you-dont-have-an-eternity-25-player]25man[/url]) - Defeat Malygos in 6 minutes or less ([i]pretty easy at 100[/i]).[/li]\n\n[li][b]A Poke in the Eye[/b] - Defeat Malygos with less than 9 players in [url=http://www.wowhead.com/achievement=1869]10-player mode[/url], or less than 21 in [url=http://www.wowhead.com/achievement=1870]25-player mode[/url] ([i]assuming you're soloing this, you get it automatically[/i]).[/li]\n\n[li][b]Denyin' the Scion[/b] ([url=http://www.wowhead.com/achievement=2148]10man[/url] / [url=http://www.wowhead.com/achievement=2149]25man[/url]) - Deliver a killing blow to a Scion of Eternity while riding on a hover disk. ([i]This is only one where you have to do something outside of just quickly killing him.  The only way to miss this is if you don't get on a dropped hover disk after killing a Scion.  Unlikely for a melee class to miss this, but a ranged class might decide to kill them all from the ground.[/i])[/li][/ul]\n\nAll of the above are required for the meta-achievement Glory of the Raider ([url=http://www.wowhead.com/achievement=2137]10man[/url] / [url=http://www.wowhead.com/achievement=2138]25man[/url]).  Once upon a time, Glory of the Raider rewarded mounts ([url=http://www.wowhead.com/item=44175/reins-of-the-plagued-proto-drake]Reins of the Plagued Proto-Drake[/url] and [url=http://www.wowhead.com/item=44164/reins-of-the-black-proto-drake]Reins of the Black Proto-Drake[/url], respectively) but the rewards have long since been removed.  The Plagued Proto-Drake now has a small chance of dropping from [url=http://www.wowhead.com/item=97565]Unclaimed Black Market Container[/url], won from [url=http://www.wowhead.com/npc=83867]Madam Goya[/url] who recently moved to the Ring of Blood in Nagrand, Draenor.  Of note, the Container can [url=http://www.wowhead.com/items?filter=cr=181:168:99;crs=1:1:12;crv=0:0:0]also drop many other rare mounts/pets[/url].  The Black Proto-Drake, at the present, can sadly no longer be obtained in any way, apparently.\n\nThe mounts that have a chance to drop from the instance itself ([item=43952], [item=43953]) are part of the very frustrating meta-achievement [b][url=http://www.wowhead.com/achievement=9713/awake-the-drakes]Awake the Drakes[/url][/b], which awards [url=http://www.wowhead.com/item=118676]Reins of the Emerald Drake[/url].  If you're just going for mounts and don't care about achievements, then might as well just run the 10-man version for the sake of quickness; the difference in drop chance is negligible between the two difficulties.", "date": "2014-12-21T20:11:38-06:00", "rating": 69, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Just brilliant. Thank you. Not only answered all my questions but also some I hadn't thought to ask.", "creationdate": "2015-05-29T11:57:18-05:00", "id": 872287, "rating": 2, "commentid": 2073965, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Wimbleton", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Just to put an updated comment: at 110 this is absolutely trivial and still worth doing for the Reins of either drake if you need them. They still drop. Malygos is often at 1HP a few seconds into phase 1, and phase 2 is just killing the scions, and then one attack on the dragon mount will finish off Malygos and the encounter.", "creationdate": "2018-06-30T13:30:01-05:00", "id": 1118533, "rating": 1, "commentid": 2073965, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "bruenir", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Note that if you kill scions too fast, the fight may bug out and never enter phase 3.", "creationdate": "2020-11-06T16:24:49-06:00", "id": 1403514, "rating": 0, "commentid": 2073965, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Malcorne", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2015-01-12T04:45:43-06:00", 11, "brownpaw"]}
