{"commentv2": 1, "number": 5, "id": 994352, "nreplies": 2, "sticky": 0, "user": "FamousAtomicBoy", "body": "Anyone else notice that he has a different voice here? It's much deeper and more regal. No offense to Cam Clarke, but I think it's far more appropriate than what you hear in the Malygos raid.", "date": "2010-03-09T15:30:55-06:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Yeah, but everyone inside that room seems to have some sort of echo upon their voices.", "creationdate": "2010-06-26T09:25:01-05:00", "id": 170027, "rating": 3, "commentid": 994352, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Zanzari", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "It's actually still Cam Clarke (the actor who voiced him in Eye of Eternity), just with a different effect. Listen closely:  /script PlaySoundFile(\"Sound\\\\Creature\\\\Malygos\\\\UR_Malygos_YSVisTwo01.wav\")", "creationdate": "2010-09-06T16:50:30-05:00", "id": 180775, "rating": 2, "commentid": 994352, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "Magnett", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 6, "id": 1346719, "nreplies": 6, "sticky": 0, "user": "Roseita", "body": "Dragons just have to take on attractive forms every time they go around as mortals. I'm not complaining, no siree, but still, I'm waiting for a not-so-attractive troll/orc/dwarf/ect. ect. to turn out to be a dragon breaking tradition of taking on lovely forms. Deathwing is the exeption to this, however. Either way, for now, it's all good, because let's face it, Malygos in his old humanoid (elvenoid?) form is not that bad looking.", "date": "2011-02-23T01:31:40-06:00", "rating": 6, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Well...you have Chromie as a Gnome, though shes not an Aspect", "creationdate": "2011-10-08T21:06:14-05:00", "id": 269590, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1346719, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "Arraya", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "WoW kept a pretty classic part of draconic tropery--that is, dragons are pretty egotistical and like to be admired! As for Chromie, she's cute enough that it makes up for the lack of mainstream hawt. Also, hilarious.", "creationdate": "2012-07-19T22:17:16-05:00", "id": 558083, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1346719, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "MiltiadesBooga", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "There's also a Goblin form dragon in Badlands, sent by Alexstraza to save a black dragon egg. Its a quest chain, from that egg will born Whration", "creationdate": "2013-01-02T00:04:30-06:00", "id": 618194, "rating": 4, "commentid": 1346719, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "mannex", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "I don't know, Kalecgos is kinda stocky and chubby in his human form, and somehow Wrathion has wrinkles as an adolescent.", "creationdate": "2014-06-13T03:48:09-05:00", "id": 751027, "rating": 0, "commentid": 1346719, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 256, "username": "cephadex", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Kairozdormu, the bronze dragon that took Garrosh back to old Draenor and started all this crap chose an orc as his humanoid form.", "creationdate": "2015-09-12T23:16:24-05:00", "id": 898587, "rating": 1, "commentid": 1346719, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "propyro", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 0, "id": 349722, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "186578", "body": "Bit of lore on this guy, courtesy of [url=http://www.wowwiki.com/Malygos]Wowwiki[/url]:\r\n\r\n[quote]Norgannon, the Titan master-magician and keeper of lore, granted the blue dragon, Malygos, a portion of his vast power. From then on, Malygos would be known as The Spell-weaver, the guardian of magic and hidden arcanum.\r\n\r\nMalygos is a leviathan with small wings. His body is covered with crystalline scales of pure azure. His body shines with shifting colors that change constantly from blue to silver. Theoretically, since he and his children specialize in magic it is likely that their powers far exceed those of the other dragon flights since magic is the element they rule.\r\n\r\nMalygos the Spellweaver is the blue Dragon Aspect, and the master of the blue dragonflight. He is one of the most ancient creatures living on Azeroth, and one of only a handful who were alive at the time the Titans departed. Now that he has regained his sanity, he is once again taking an active role in the protection of the world.\r\n\r\nMalygos, the Lord of Magic, is said to have created magic and spells, although this is likely mere legend. His command of magic is quite impressive, rivaling that of a demigod, although he does not aspire to such power. While physically he is not as powerful as some of the other Aspects, Malygos counters this disadvantage with his phenomenal command of magic. Like most of his kind, Malygos is a solitary creature who avoids contact with others. He is believed to dwell in Northrend, in a lair filled with some of the greatest magical artifacts known to exist, including many whose powers are discussed only in hushed whispers. Returned to sanity after Deathwing\u2019s defeat at Grim Batol, Malygos now attempts to rebuild his decimated dragonflight. He spends his days studying magic, refining his abilities, and studying the various planes of the multiverse both remotely and in person, while his few remaining children scour the world for ancient artifacts and repositories of arcane power.\r\n\r\nMalygos does not seek out combat; and although he and his dragonflight are still routinely hunted by black dragons, he avoids their kind if at all possible. He protects his lair and himself with illusions and misdirection. Those who discover his home are encouraged to depart through a variety of means; Malygos takes direct action only as a last resort. When he does fight, he engages spellcasters first, using his breath weapon and other abilities to sweep spells from their minds.[/quote]\r\n\r\nHe's basically mad that the mortal races could use magic so freely, and is hostile to all users of magic. This is half the reason Dalaran moved to Northrend, the other half being able to serve as a capital for the war against the Lich King.", "date": "2008-08-11T02:25:20-05:00", "rating": 34, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
{"commentv2": 1, "number": 1, "id": 350593, "nreplies": 4, "sticky": 0, "user": "172548", "body": "I think players will not kill Malygos completely, only \"defeat\" him", "date": "2008-08-12T03:29:27-05:00", "rating": 2, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "Well as you see in the name of the acheivement you linked, ([url=http://wotlk.wowhead.com/?achievement=413]Malygos Slayer <PH> <NYI>[/url]) <PH> means [i]place holder[/i] and <NYI> means [i]not yet implemented[/i].  Which means it's not even in the game yet and they can take it out whenever they want since it's only a placeholder.", "creationdate": "2008-08-31T19:44:37-05:00", "id": 45228, "rating": 5, "commentid": 350593, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "bathazar", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Yeah but you know he's gonna live..Somehow.", "creationdate": "2008-09-03T00:38:30-05:00", "id": 45437, "rating": 4, "commentid": 350593, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "173862", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "The Eye of Eternity was only a setback.", "creationdate": "2009-07-17T14:54:54-05:00", "id": 110299, "rating": 12, "commentid": 350593, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "410715", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "read Thrall: Twilight of the Aspects  and you will find out what happens", "creationdate": "2011-08-08T00:12:44-05:00", "id": 257285, "rating": 0, "commentid": 350593, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "yom125", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr"