{"commentv2": 1, "number": 7, "id": 379135, "nreplies": 10, "sticky": 0, "user": "Vorph", "body": "It's been confirmed from the various quotes that he and Alexstrazsa uses, Malygos will be definitely slain. This is actually a mortal blow to the lore for the death of an Aspect is a tremendous impact on the whole world. Let's see how Blizzard will get over this.\r\n\r\nQuotes of Malygos from the fight can be found here:\r\n\r\nhttp://www.wowwiki.com/Malygos_(tactics)", "date": "2008-09-17T18:08:46-05:00", "rating": 13, "indent": 0, "roles": 0, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [{"body": "If you read the lore about what aspects in fact are you would realize that the Aspects were empowered by the titans with great [b][i]control[/i][/b] over their respective aspects in order for them to watch over Azeroth. Nozdormu watches over time, and Malygos watches over and keeps the use of magic in the world under control ( which is why he is so !@#$ed at mortal magic users ). While they do have great control over their aspect they are not by any means the physical manifestation of it.  While it is kinda far fetched to kill an aspect (but that is solved by the fact that we recieve a large a", "creationdate": "2008-09-17T18:08:47-05:00", "id": 365003, "rating": 9, "commentid": 379135, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "192628", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Well, I suspect it won't be as major a blow on lore as you think. See, only on Azeroth would it be effected(because the dragons aren't much older than when the Titan's came to Azeroth, and places like Draenor and Argus existed with magic way before then), people in places like Outland wouldn't notice much of a difference. But, this would be a smaller impact to Azeroth than if say Alexstraza were to die, not just because of what aspect she is, but also because of the origin of mana. I can imagine bliz stating that the Sunwell and some kind of source in Dalaran empowered all of Azeroth, but I ca", "creationdate": "2008-09-17T18:08:47-05:00", "id": 356720, "rating": 4, "commentid": 379135, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "184400", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Its true though, that it's really silly we have to kill him.  And it's like all the aspects have gone mad all of a sudden. Malygos wanting to pwn the heck out of every mage in Azeroth, Ysera nightmaring away, Neltharion... well ya know, and Nozdormu isn't doing much better (not spoiling though :p).  We really shouldn't be killing this guy :(", "creationdate": "2008-11-27T20:33:15-06:00", "id": 59910, "rating": 3, "commentid": 379135, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "10128", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "'Time is literaly nozdomu's body for example, and that's why time would disapoear if he was slain.' funny how the 1st thing The Highfather did after empowering him to guard time was show him his own [b]death[/b] then huh ?", "creationdate": "2008-12-01T22:32:34-06:00", "id": 61086, "rating": 2, "commentid": 379135, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "miko1", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}, {"body": "Are you sure he is dead? All you have seen is his body falling into endless Eye of Eternity... place without limits", "creationdate": "2008-12-03T07:23:30-06:00", "id": 61481, "rating": 5, "commentid": 379135, "dataTree": 1, "roles": 0, "username": "263049", "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "downvotedByUser": false, "reportedByUser": false, "votedByUser": false}], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}}
